This setting is for newcomers, for veteran players, for X-COM enthusiasts and for JOHN CENA. No, seriously start with this difficulty, once you get a hang of it you are free to move up.
X-Division is meant to be played the way you want it to play, but we recommend a voluntary ironman playthrough without using the ironman option.

Read the easy difficulty description.
This difficulty is for players who have a 20 year experience in X-COM, played the hell out of any other X-COM or XCOM game, played Long War on the insane diificulty and beat it with ease, or who grasped the basic principles of X-Division, and beat the second phase of the game with a good prospect of continuation.

Read the easy difficulty description.
The mod was created for this difficulty and the aliens will operate at 100%% efficiency. This is the difficulty for balance testers. Select this difficulty if you have a decent amount of experience and want to feel the intended experience head on and dont fear the consequences.

Read the easy difficulty. It is not recommended to play this game on this difficulty.
This is insane. If you beat the game and still havent felt the burn already you can try this difficulty. Its just a harder version of veteran.

Iron Man Mode: This mode forces the player to live with their mistakes, providing for more tension. If Iron Man mode is active, the player cannot manually save their game or load previous progress. Instead, the game autosaves after every major event and on game exit, overwriting the previous autosave each time. Once you have a few games under your belt, we recommend giving it a try! This mod in still in beta for testing and save games can help us to find bugs more efficiently. If you wish to help in that regard, then ironman mode is not recommended. You can otherwise simulate it by only saving at the end of a session.

Following our study of Alien Phaser Pistols and Rifles we've gained a basic understanding of how they work.
With just a little more time and analysis, I'm sure we'll be able to incorporate them into our own energy weapon designs.

We've successfully completed our research on the Alien Phaser and Lightning weapons Commander.
Now, with my towering intellect and a little help from one of your Caesan captives we believe we can increase our understanding of and start to develop our first energy based weapons.
Leave us for now, I'll call you as soon as I've extracted everything I need from that Caesan Weapon Sergeant.

An energy based alien handgun. We need to study this so as we can start developing our own energy based weapons.
Bring me as many of these types of weapons as you can find Commander, every little helps.

An energy based alien rifle. Further analysis should help us to understand it's secrets and create our own energy weapons.
Try to find some more variants on this design for me Commander.

An alien machine gun capable of firing energy based rounds. This should really help further our understanding of energy based weapons.
Now, if you'll excuse me, I need some time to study this...

Following our study of Alien Lightning pistols and the initial questioning of that Caesan Weapon Sergeant you so helpfully captured for us, I believe we're making progress on increasing our understanding of alien energy based weaponry
Bring me to that weapon sergeant you captured Commander, there's a few details I want to make sure of first.

Your troops recovered this curious weapon and naturally brought it to me Commander to figure out how it works.
It appears to discharge primarily electrical energy resulting in paralysis or shutdown of the target.
We can't replicate this design, however, by taking it apart and studying it I'm sure I'll be able to invent new weaponry based on it or at the least use parts of it.

An interesting weapon commander, a longer range version of its pistol relative
Study of this will surely help us in developing technologies for focusing electrical discharges over long distances
But for now, we need to concentrate on extracting as much useful information and parts from it as we can.

A very powerful electrical weapon Commander, be careful while around it.
This will destroy any vehicle it manages to hit or completely paralyze one of our soldiers.
We really need to study this to further our knowledge of electrical based weaponry, plus we can probably use parts of this weapon in future designs.

While examining the pistols and rifles you've brought us, one of my techs stumbled upon the idea of replacing parts of our existing light weapons with parts from the alien versions.
It didn't work as planned, the test subject suffered horrible injuries.
But now that I'm on the job we should be able to get this project up and running in no time.

We've had a stroke of luck Commander. One of my technicians was present during your recent interrogation of that Sebillian Weapon Sergeant.
He informed me of what he overheard, and using our existing knowledge of alien ballistics and my natural genius, I've come up with some ideas to further our understanding of Alien Ballistic Weaponry which may potentially enable us to enhance our own designs.
It appears to be similar in function to our own pistols. I'm sure we can strip it for parts we can use in our future designs.
Very akin to our own assault rifles. Lets take it apart and see what we can make use of.
A long range version of their standard ballistic weapons. We'll study it and make use of what we can.
It's almost like a shotgun, isn't it? Study of this should allow us to improve our own designs

Do you feel lucky Commander, well do you?
Sorry, forgive my joke, which appears to have gone right over your head in any case.
Further analysis of this weapon should provide some ideas for making our own versions.

This appears to be a very dangerous weapon to be on the wrong end of Commander.
Studying its construction may enable us to incorporate similar principles into our own designs.

I'm a genius Commander! No really!
During an interrogation of a Sebillian Weapon Sergeant we pointed one of his flamer rifles at him. You wouldn't believe how talkative he became.
We now just need to go over the notes we took during this conversation and implement it into our own weapon theories.

Taking what we already know about the Alien Heavy Flamer weapons and what we've gained from interrogating their bearers, I've developed a working theory that will significantly enhance our understanding of incendiary weaponry.
I still need to prove it, but have no doubts that I am once again correct in my deductions.

An alien incendiary device. Further study of this should allow us to understand Alien Flamers.
We could do with more samples to work with Commander, so go get some!
Similar to our terrestial flame-thrower, though more compact in design. With enough analysis I'm sure we'll gain an understanding of how they operate.

A fearsome weapon commander, please put it down gently, I'm rather attached to my eyebrows.
We'll take it apart carefully and try to avoid any accidental explosions, but I'm positive our analysis of this will further our understanding of incendiary weapon design.

This appears to be a cross between a shotgun and a flamethrower. Quite deadly at close range.
We need to examine this in detail and hopefully find a way to utilize its concepts in future designs.

Well Commander I've done it! You can thank me now if you wish.
Following our exhaustive analysis of alien ballistic weaponry I compiled a list of parts which we can use to invent our own upgraded weapons.
Now, if you'll forgive me, I need to take some time to find a way to explain this process to those apes in the workshops ... and to patent this design

Sorry Commander, I was busy on the phone talking to my publicist.
After the successful implementation of my patented X-Division designs, I've been busy reviewing your operational field reports to see if they can be improved upon.
Using my genius level intellect I've come up with a way to do just that. All that remains is to carry out some tests and to contact the Nobel Prize Committee.
We're going to take a 9mm Beretta and apply our upgrades to it. I expect it to have increased stopping power at the cost of slightly reduced range.

With my pistol and rifle design being such a huge success, I've decided to apply the process to an Ingram Mac-10.
Don't forget to let your men know who to thank for this.

Your soldiers are always going on about how great the M-16 is. Well wait till they see what I propose to replace it with.
It will have increased range and damage by the time I'm done with it and then your men can go on about how amazing I am instead.

Your standard 12-gauge shotguns not providing enough oomph for you. I expect this revised design to provide at least 50 percent more.
Just remember to fire it up-close

Following on from our improved rifle, we have plans for upgrading the M2010 sniper rifle. We should be able to increase its range, damage and clip size.
Your men know where to find me to share their appreciation.

An upgraded version of the FN M249 SAW. This monster of a heavy machine gun will have increased range and stopping power per shot, not to mention the sheer sound of it firing will likely scare your opposition stiff.

With our improved sniper rifles and cannons making such an impact, I thought we could try something different.
I took an M134 minigun and have successfully come up with a plan for integrating my improvements with it.
Your grunts were complaining about lack of firepower. This should shut them up.
We've come up with a design for a handheld high-calibre cannon. It's a powerful weapon, but heavy, so only your strongest will be allowed to take one from the armoury.
A new and improved version of the MK-1 pistol. We're replacing the old firing mechanism and barrel which will hopefully lead to increased range and penetration
An upgraded version of the MK-1 SMG. It's now capable of firing Armour Piercing rounds.
We've improved the MK-1 Assault rifle. It's now capable of firing Armour Piercing rounds.
By applying my latest invention to the MK-1 shotgun we believe we can increase it's power.
Like shooting things from a distance? Then you're going to love the upgrades we have planned for our MK-1 sniper rifle.
If you thought the MK-1 HMG was scary, wait till you get a load of this baby!
This should really be mounted on a helicopter, but if you can carry it, it'll work better than the MK-1 minigun.
You didn't think it was possible did you? But due to my brainpower we've come up a way to increase our cannons stopping power.
Applying what we've learned from our Sebillian captives, I believe we can fine-tune the MK-2 pistol to be even more efficient.
The MK-2 SMG was good, but if what we've uncovered from the Sebillians is true, then the MK-3 will be even better.
Those Sebillians seem to have an in-depth understanding of ballistic weapons. I believe we can upgrade the MK-2 Rifle with what we've pried from them.
A few tweaks to the MK-2 shotgun design should improve it's performance based on what our analysts have managed to translate of Sebillian files.
What we've learned about Sebillian vision from our recent hacking has led to an improved sight for our sniper rifles. We'll begin testing immediately.
The MK-1 HMG was a beast. The MK-2 was even more impressive. But after going over the information retrieved from our Sebillian captives, I believe I can improve upon it.

If this works, which it will seeing as I designed it, I expect at least a commendation from you Commander.
We've taken what was recovered from the Sebillian Data we hacked and come up with a way to use it to improve the MK-2 minigun.
Oh ... I'd like a medal too.

Those neanderthals in Engineering finally did something useful, by accident naturally. While manufacturing a MK-2 Cannon, they mistakenly put in one of the parts backwards.
The resulting weapon didn't work of course, but when we examined it I came up with an ingenious idea based on what we learned about Sebillian firearms which should improve the performance of the MK-2 cannon.

I think we've finally done it Commander! Based on our research of Alien Phaser Technology, I've come up with a theory for creating our own energy based weaponry.
We still need to test it of course, but I expect to have it operational very soon.

Welcome Commander, I'm glad you stopped by.
Subsequent to our development of Laser Technology and with a little ingenuity from myself, I believe we can further increase the power of our laser arsenal.
I'd like to go over the notes we took from recent Advanced Alien Phaser acquisitions just to make sure.
Now .... if you could just sign this expenses form, we'll get started.

We've come up with a design for a pistol which fires coherent light at it's target.
Sorry, I should have said energy, stop looking at me like that.

While we've managed to successfully invent laser pistols and rifles, some of your recruits were complaining about having to use standard 12 gauge shotguns.
Well I have a plan to remedy that!
A slightly larger version of our laser pistol design which can focus energy over longer distances due to .... I won't bore you with the details, I can already see your eyes glazing over.

Some of your men were saying that they'd like to keep some more distance between themselves and the ET's, which is understandable.
I've come up with a design for a sniper rifle version of our standard laser rifle which might interest them.

We already managed to produce a weapon capable of emitting short bursts of energy, however we're having difficulty creating one that can emit them in constant bursts.
For now, I have a blueprint for a cannon type laser which we hope to be able to modify to a rapid-fire version in the future.
Yes, I know the name "gatling" doesn't make a lot of sense right now Commander, but unfortunately it was patented using that name, so we're stuck with it.
Combining what we've learned from our precision and gatling versions of laser weaponry, I believe we can create a devastating laser weapon, but it will be quite heavy.
I think we've come up with an enhancement for our standard laser pistol. I suspect we'll be able to produce one with slightly increased range and penetration.
We believe we can enhance the damage output of our laser shotgun. It'll still be very short range though, so remind your troops to be careful.

With our new understanding of laser technology, I think we can improve upon our standard laser rifle.
Call it MK-2 if you must, but it should have increased range and penetration.

Our increased understanding of laser technology has given me a few ideas regarding upgrading our sniper rifles.
Simply put, i think it'll have better range, penetration and stopping power!

I think I've found a way to increase the light output through the len .... Commander?
Ok, in laymans terms i believe i can increase the damage our MK-1 version causes.
Yes, it's still called "Gatling", no it doesn't have rapid fire capabilities, but we're very close to achieving that now.

There isn't a lot we can do to improve upon our original minigun design.
BUT
I think we can modify it's feed belt and perhaps increase its armour penetration

The information we learned from the Caesan's has given me an idea for upgrading our MK-2 laser pistol.
If this works, it should have slightly higher energy output, range and penetration.

Based on the information we stole from the Caesan's, I believe we can make some tweaks to our MK-2 Laser design.
I expect it to have a slightly increased range and clip size when completed

We've learned a thing or two from that recent hacking attempt on the Caesan Databank.
With this new knowledge we can improve upon our original MK-2 laser rifle.
Increased range, damage and less recoil which should improve accuracy, what more could your troops ask for Commander!

Would you like a laser rifle with almost double the penetration of the MK-2 sniper version Commander?
Well, thanks to the Caesan's I believe we can achieve this! Won't they be happy to know how they're helping our war effort.

With what we've uncovered from the Caesan's we might finally be able to create a laser capable of sustained bursts of energy.
A laser HMG if you like, although it will likely have slightly less energy output per shot than the MK-2.
Now everyone can stop laughing at the name!

Scattered among that data you pulled from the Caesan's was some intriguing information on energy manipulation.
I believe we can use this to increase the general performance of our MK-2 laser minigun.
It'll still be heavy Commander, this thing wasn't really designed to be carried by a soldier.

We've now studied a number of these new plasma type weapons the aliens are carrying and have arrived at some worrying conclusions.
Either the aliens are improving their own technology as this war goes on, or they had these all the time and we were lucky they weren't used against us at the outset.
Either way, our own path is certain, we must find a way to use or adapt this technology into our own weaponry if we wish to prevail.

We've had a bit of good fortune smile on us commander.
While interrogating that Caesan Weapon Officer about the use of one of their higher-end energy weapons, he let slip that they both have some basis in weaponised plasma.
Using this new information, I believe we can further our own understanding of plasma generation by integrating certain aspects of alien neutron technology into it.
If this works we should be able to improve our current plasma weaponry.

This pistol appears to be an upgrade of their phaser design.
It still emits energy beams, but they appear to be of a more damaging composition.
Further analysis of this is needed to generate theories on it's composition.

This weapon appears to be of a bull-pup rifle configuration.
The increase in damage they display over their earlier phaser weaponry is worrying and further study is required if we wish to understand how they operate.

An alien assault rifle utilising their new plasma energy.
We'll need to take it apart and study it's internal mechanisms to gain a better understanding of them. Perhaps we'll find parts we can use in our own weapon designs.

Testing on this weapon to date has indicated that it propels plasma at a higher velocity than it's smaller counterparts, resulting in far greater armour penetration so try not to get hit by one Commander.
Study of how it achieves this will almost certainly help us in understanding the principles of this technology and hopefully allow us to increase the effectiveness of our own weaponry.

This is the long range version of their plasma weaponry.
With a bit of luck, study of it's modular design may give us a clearer insight into alien plasma technologies
Barring that, it's at least much easier to deconstruct and obtain useable parts from than lesser models.

This weapon is almost a rocket launcher. It projects plasma with such force that it also causes damage to the immediate area around the point of impact.
Study of how it achieves this should allow us to increase our knowledge of how plasma weaponry works in general ... plus the dismantled parts may come in useful too.

You really don't want to stand in front of one of these Commander. Preliminary testing has shown that it spits out energy at a very high rate.
If we can understand how it achieves this we may well be able to use that information to further increase our knowledge on the principles of plasma generation.

While their plasma technology appears to involve charging ions, study of their neutron weapons suggests that they instead manipulate neutrons via some form of fusion to produce the energy beams emitted.
I can't help but feel that these two weapon principles are linked but further analysis will be required to establish their commonalities.
I think we should start by re-examining the notes we took during interrogation of their bearers.

This weapon fires a slightly different type of beam than their plasma equivalent resulting in better armour penetration.
We'll need to take it apart and study its components to find out how they achieved this.

Focusing an energy beam consisting of neutrons over such a long distance should be impossible.
All attempts to replicate this in our labs have met with failure, so for now we're forced to dismantle these weapons and attempt to integrate certain key components into our own weapons.

We really need to discover how the aliens have managed to focus the beams fired by these weapons.
Until then though, we can strip it for parts for use in our own technology.

This is the heavy hitter among their neutron based weaponry. I'd really suggest not standing in its way.
Study of this may lead to an increased understanding of neutron manipulation.

The introduction of these toxin weapons have made terror assaults all the more damaging to our reputation.
We really have to come up with a counter-measure to these insidious weapons to restore the balance.
Unfortunately, that requires gaining a greater understanding of how they work first, which while distasteful, is necessary.

This pistol fires small hollow rounds filled with a type of organic chemical.
Further analysis is required to determine this chemicals structure and properties and perhaps find a way to utilise it.

These toxin weapons appear to have been designed primarily for dispatching organic life.
The actual chemical used is still unknown to us, and needs to be studied further to counter it.

The existence of this weapon will cause widespread panic among the public if they learn of it.
Its toxin appears to attack the central nervous system of any organic lifeform it enters.
If we study this it may lead to a way to neutralise this or at least turn it on the aliens.

This weapon fires its projectiles with enough velocity that it causes some of the toxin to vaporise upon impact, affecting the area around it.
Further study of this may lead to us being able to improve upon our own chemical gas weaponry.

Now that we have a basic understanding of how Alien Plasma Technology works, I think we can start working on adapting those principles to our own energy weaponry.
We may not be able to completely create all required parts from scratch, but using specific components from captured alien energy weapons should be able to cover any shortfall.
If successful, this will likely render our entire laser arsenal obsolete.

Following deeper analysis of alien plasma technology we've come up with some theories on how to improve our own energy based plasma weapons.
These theories still need to be tested of course, but I'm confident that we'll be able to improve upon our initial designs. I am a genius afterall.

A pistol based on our new plasma technology.
It's still in the testing phase, but initial results look promising, demonstrating twice the energy output over its laser counterpart.

Integrating plasma technology with a rifle design has proven challenging, but we're almost there.
I think you'll be really impressed with the increased damage it causes compared to the laser version.
Now, if you'll excuse me, we need to carry out some more tweaks to the firing mechanism.

Focusing a beam of plasma energy over a long distance is difficult ... In fact we're still working on achieving it.
It might end up with a shorter range than a laser sniper rifle, but each round will be far more powerful.

Given the difficulties we faced with developing a rapid fire laser weapon, I'm pleasantly surprised to say that making a plasma variant was relatively simple.
Our tech in charge of filing patents for all my inventions decided to play it safe this time and use the term caster instead of gatling, but rest assured it still works.
Well, it almost works, we still need to design a suitable casing to house all the required parts.

We've come up with a design for a cannon type weapon based on our plasma technology.
Once finished, it should be capable of firing highly energised beams of plasma which will likely cause damage to anything adjacent to its target as well.

I think we can increase the energy output of our plasma pistol by replacing it's focusing device with its equivalent from an alien energy weapon.
This may require a redesign of some other parts, but i think the result will be worth the effort.

By swapping some of our rifles firing mechanism with similar components from alien energy rifles, we should be able to increase its damage output per shot, and perhaps even its overall accuracy.
We'll get to work on a prototype right away.

If we increase the power provided to the plasma generator we could theoretically increase the damage caused per shot.
Unfortunately we're at the limit of what we can achieve using terrestrial technology, but we might be able to adapt some alien energy weapon cores to suit our design.

Due to it's rapid-fire nature, the capacitors tend to over-heat after sustained use.
If we introduce a cooling mechanism we found in alien energy weapons we might be able to avert this leading to a higher rate of fire.

We think we can make some improvements to our plasma cannon based on our increased understanding of plasma technology.
If our theories are correct, we should be able to improve its energy output, thus increasing impact and splash damage.
We're also going to replace the firing mechanism with parts from alien weapons which should make it a little easier to fire and help with accuracy issue too.

The data uncovered from the Caesans in our latest hacking attempt contained a detailed schematic of one of the more mysterious components found in their energy weapons.
We now fully understand it's uses and can attempt to integrate into our pistol design. If successful it should increase the range, power and shots per clip.

Thanks to the information we deciphered from the Caesan databank, we now know how their thermal generators work.
Installing one of these in our MK-2 rifle should increase its range, energy output and rounds per clip.

The files stolen from the Caseans contained the information on long range plasma focus which had eluded us.
Using this and replacing a few parts in the MK-2 should enable us to rectify its range problem and as a by-product make each round more powerful and require less charge to generate.

Would you like an upgraded plasma caster with higher range and damage all while being able to hold more rounds per clip?
Of course you would, and I'm happy to oblige. We've gone over the data stolen from the Caesans and have come up with a series of tweaks to the MK-2 which will hopefully achieve our aims.
Don't forget to remind your men who to thank, and no, i don't mean the caesans.

Based on information stolen from the caesans we've come up with some tweaks for our mk.2 plasma cannon.
We believe we can refine the beam generation which will theoretically allow it to hit targets at longer ranges, while also increasing its overall damage but requiring less charge per shot, meaning more rounds per clip.

Study of the basic alien matergy weapons has lead us to deduce the manner in which they operate.
They appear to force their projectiles from the gun by means of a strong unknown field capable of transferring it's stored kinetic energy to the matter of the projectile, hence the term matergy, literally pushing it out at unheard of speeds.
Further study is required if we ever wish to utilise this concept in our own weaponry.

While interrogating a sebillian weapon officer about their more advanced matergy weapons he said something which didn't really make any sense to us at the time regarding flamer technology.
After that i spent some time going back over our notes on their higher-end flamer weaponry and noticed that they share a couple of components with matergy weapons.
We still don't know exactly where this will lead, but hopefully with a deeper understanding of matergy technology we'll be able to improve our own designs.

The aliens have started carrying some new handguns into battle.
We'll need to take this apart and see if we can determine how it functions.

These new weapons appear to have innate armour penetration due to the velocity at which the projectile flies.
Closer study is required to see if we can emulate this.

There doesn't appear to be any propellant contained in the ammunition for these weapons.
We're really mystified as to how they fire at all and require more samples of this type of weaponry to better understand its properties.

A long range version of their rifle design, capable of firing projectiles at an even higher velocity.
Closer study of it's components may further our understanding of how this is achieved.

A bulkier version of their matergy assault rifle, this is capable of firing multiple projectiles extremely rapidly.
Further examination of its components may enable us to integrate something similar into our designs.

Commander, could you sign this expenses form for me, we need a new proton magnetometer. Our previous one blew up while measuring the field oscillations triggered by firing this weapon.
If we can figure out how it manages to fluctuate its kinetic energy field so quickly I'm sure it would further our understanding of Alien Matergy weapons immensely.

This is an unusual example of matergy weaponry Commander, not so much in its function but in it's results.
Because of it's bulk it's capable of containing a device capable of generating larger kinetic energy fields, which enable it to fire bulkier projectiles at comparable velocities to it's smaller counterparts.
The extra impact area of this projectile and it's velocity tends to cause a small thermal reaction at the point of impact.
It explodes Commander, it explodes. All without any additional materials required for the projectile.
Being able to harness this power would be very beneficial for our own weaponry. Maybe with a little more study ...

Study of the basic alien matergy weapons has lead us to conclude that we don't have the requisite technology to copy them, but we have deduced a manner in which we might be able to emulate them.
I won't bore you with the details, but if we can create a compact device capable of generating a strong enough electro-magnetic field we should be able to create weaponry similar in function to alien matergy designs.
This will be a major breakthrough in ballistic technology if correct, and could potentially even be scaled up to work with aircraft and vehicle weapons, but we still need to figure out a few key components.

With our now deeper understanding of Alien Matergy Technology I believe we can upgrade our own Electromagnetic technology designs.
You look confused commander? Oh ... we shortened the name to Mag Technology because watching your troops try to remember its full name when requisitioning weapons pained me.
By stripping alien matergy weapons of certain components and integrating them with our current designs, we should be able to increase the EM field generated in the weaponry, resulting in higher damage output.
Of course, this is all still theoretical at this stage and needs to be fully lab tested, but given my genius level intellect, I'm positive i'll be able to make it work.

This is a prototype pistol utilising our new MAG Technology.
In testing so far it has demonstrated slightly increased range, damage and penetration over its predecessors and we think it'll also be capable of short 3-round burst fire as well.
Unfortunately, we're having a little trouble condensing the field generator into a package small enough to fit it's size, but with a little more work we should manage it.

We have designs for a new rifle utilising our MAG technology.
Once completed, I fully expect it to outdo the performance of our division rifles in every aspect.

Integrating MAG Technology into a shotgun has proven problematic.
By its very nature, MAG Technology works by forcing a metallic object along a path using EM fields, which doesn't really translate very well to a cartridge based weapon.
We're still working on this Commander and think we have a solution which involves demodulating the field. This will likely result in a shorter range than other MAG weaponry, but it's probably the best we can do right now.

With assault rifles already taken care of, we've turned our attention to sniper rifles.
Our precision rifles have always been designed with utilising our highest velocity concepts in mind. As such, while you won't see a marked improvement in damage per round, the smaller diameter of the projectile will result in an increase in armour penetration.
This has also allowed us to fit more rounds per clip and enable a semi-automatic firing mode.
We're still working on the generator to achieve this field switching with a minimum of input from your troops. Ideally we'll make it so that the flick of a switch will toggle between firing modes. I'll call you when it's completed.

Our testing of this HMG we've redesigned using MAG Technology was delayed by a problem with the carbine version, but now that's been sorted, we can finish it.
Once complete it should prove to be a general upgrade compared to the Division HMG.
I hear your men have taken to nicknaming it MAG Storm due to the hail of projectiles it spits out!

Based on concepts from our MAG Storm and precision rifles, we've come up with a design for a MAG minigun.
Using the EM field to help with the spinning of the barrels has enabled us to almost double it's rpm.
The downside to this is the field generator itself is quite bulky and weighty. However, I'm sure you'll have some troops strong enough to carry it.
Just make sure it's pointed in the general direction of the aliens before you pull the trigger.

By replacing some of the internal workings of our Mag Pistol with alien components we believe we can increase the EM field generated.
This should result in higher damage and armour penetration per shot fired.

Alien Matergy components are capable of increasing the power of the field created by our EM generators.
In theory swapping them with certain parts in our Mag rifle design should increase its damage and armour penetration.

I think we've found a way to increase both the cartidge capacity and pellet count per cartridge by increasing the power held by the EM field using alien capacitors.
Unfortunately, the combination of both increased pellets to impel along with an increased EM field strength have cancelled each other out as regards improving its range.
However the damage boost per shot fired should be more than enough to keep your troops happy.

Utilising alien matergy components, we've come up with some tweaks to our original Mag sniper rifle.
This should result in increased armour penetration and damage per projectile.
We've also redesigned the scope to enable improved accuracy at long ranges.

As with all our other MK-2 upgrades, replacing a few key components with Alien Matergy parts has allowed us to increase the EM field generated.
When completed it should be capable of greater armour penetration and damage per round along with a slight increase in accuracy.

A few small tweaks to the Mag minigun should enable us to increase its damage.
We hope to achieve this by substituting the timing mechanism with one of alien design, thus slightly increasing the amount of energy imparted to each and every projectile.
It was dangerous before, now it'll be deadly!

Based on information retrieved from an encrypted file on a sebillian computer, we've come with a few modifications for the mk-2 mag pistol which might interest you.
By modifying the projectiles and barrel, I believe we can increase their range and armour penetration along with potentially being able to fire 4 rounds in semi-auto mode as opposed to 3.
We still need to finalise testing on this concept before we can go to production, but it shouldn't take much longer now.

We have plans for improving the mk-2 rifles rate of fire, armour penetration and range.
Unfortunately, I can't take all the credit for these improvements as some of it came from information stored on a sebillian computer, which we were recently able to access.
We still need to carry out tests on these upgrades, but I'll call you as soon as it's ready.

Commander! We've finally managed to increase the range of our Mag shotgun. Not by much, but I'm sure it will make a difference to your troops survivability.
Thanks to the data we stole from the sebillians, we were able to significantly increase the EM field output, which has led to increased range, cartridge count and pellets per cartridge.
Unfortunately there is a slight field stability issue which we're still working on correcting. It should be fixed soon.

Our recent hacking attempt on the sebillian databanks unlocked some information regarding high-velocity rounds.
If we combine this with our current Mag precision rifle design I believe we can produce one with increased range, armour penetration and damage per round.
What more could your snipers ask for?

We have some plans for upgrading our mk-2 mag HMG based on a sebillian ballistics report we recently decrypted.
If what they appear to say is true, then we should be able to reduce the diameter of the projectiles fired, thus resulting in increased ammo capacity along with a higher rate of fire due to the reduced cross-section of ... ok, i'll stop there before you fall asleep.
Essentially you will do more damage in the same amount of time, happy?
Now, i'd like to get this testing finished ...

We thought our Mk-2 Mag minigun was as good as it could get, but with a little unwitting help from the sebillians we've come up with a few tweaks to its design.
If all goes according to plan it will be capable of a higher rate of fire along with increased ammo capacity which should result in a significant increase in the devastation caused when you pull the trigger.
Also, a side effect of the ammunition modification is that they can travel further and will penetrate armour with more ease than previous versions.
We're still correcting the timing mechanism to handle these changes, but it'll be worth the wait.

Gauss or "coil-gun" technology has been around since the turn of the century, but has always been held back due to scaling and power supply issues.
Following our research into alien vindicator technology however, i believe we can now make the production of hand-held weapons utilising gaussian principles a reality.
WE still need to iron out the power supply issues, but once done we can start developing our own weapons that will be at least the equal of those carried by the aliens.

Now that we've successfully developed a technology capable of creating small arms utilising gauss principles, I believe we can start to work on refining our knowledge of how these weapons operate.
following our successful research into advanced alien vindicator technology, I think that with a little more study, we'll be able to upgrade our existing gauss weaponry.

We've come up with a design for a pistol based on our Gauss technology.
Acceleration and thus range of any gauss weapon is limited by the length of the barrel, so this won't be a long-range weapon, but should provide slightly longer range and higher damage than a MAG pistol once complete.

We have a plan to try to incorporate the rapid fire capabilities of our gauss rifle with the small form factor of our gauss pistol.
Once completed it should be able to fire bursts comparable in damage to the rifle, but the reduced barrel length will hamper its range.

We're working on adapting a rifle to use our Gauss technology.
It technically won't be a rifle anymore due to the barrel not being rifled, but we didn't want to over-confuse your troops so kept the name
Compared to the Mag rifle, It should provide for greater range and damage per projectile once completed.

gauss technology doesn't really lend itself to shotgun type weapons, but your assault troops were complaining about not having the latest technology at their disposal.
While it's barrel will be almost as long as that of a rifle, the fact that it's accelerating multiple objects at the same time limits the amount of energy per object, thus reducing its effective range.
Once completed however, it should prove far more effective at close range than the mag shotgun.

By lengthening the barrel of our gauss rifle design, i believe we can create a viable gauss sniper rifle.
Initial testing has shown that the lengthened barrel seriously increases the velocity of the projectile and our projections indicate that it will have longer range and be roughly twice as powerful as a Mag precision rifle once completed.

We're trying to adapt our HMG's to utilise gauss technology but have run into a snag or two.
Chiefly the coils tend to over-heat when under constant use. We're currently developing a new timing mechanism to alternate between coils which seems to be effective but requires further testing.
As with all our gauss weaponry, we expect it to have a longer range and higher damage than its MAG predecessor.

By combining what we've learned from the development of shotguns, sniper rifles and HMG's using gauss technology, we've come up with a prototype for a gauss minigun.
Once completed it should be capable of dealing twice the damage per round compared to the MAG minigun, but will fire less rounds per burst due to the huge increase in power required.

From our increased understanding of gauss technology, we've come up with a revised design for the gauss pistol.
By swapping out certain parts with alien ballistic cores, we believe we can increase its range, damage and armour penetration.

With what we've learned by studying advanced applications of gauss technology we think we can improve our original SMG.
Once complete it should be capable of increased range and damage per shot. We're also redesigning the projectile to enhance it's armour penetration.

Our research into Advanced gauss technology has given us some ideas for upgrading our rifle design.
By using parts from alien weaponry in place of our own, we believe we can increase its range, armour penetration and damage per projectile.

Advancements in gauss technology have provided us with a way in which we can enhance the original gauss shotgun.
It will still be short range, but by replacing some key parts, we believe we can increase the power generated per coil and thus impel more pellets per round.
This increased force should also provide some degree of armour penetration at close range.

Due to their long barrel sniper rifle designs seem custom made for gauss technology, and with our recent advancements in this field, we believe we can further improve on them.
With the use of alien ballistic cores in place of certain parts of our original design, we should be able to achieve far greater range and accuracy, and our redesigned projectile should achieve far more armour penetration and damage per shot.

Based on what we've learned from research into advanced gauss technology, we've come up with a few tweaks for our HMG.
Using parts from alien weapons in place of some of our own, we think we can increase its range.
We're also redesigning the projectile to achieve greater penetration and damage per round.

Even with our research into advanced gauss technology complete, there's little we can do to improve on our original minigun design.
But with some modifications to the coils we might be able to increase the damage and armour penetration per round slightly, along with making it more accurate to fire.

With information gained from recent hacking attempts on sebillian computers, we've come up with some modifications for the mk-2 pistol.
If this works, it should further increase its range, armour penetration and possibly even damage per round.

We've obtained some new ballistics data from a sebillian file we managed to decrypt.
Using this information we believe we can upgrade our smg to achieve a longer range, along with increased armour penetration.

Sebillians seem to have quite extensive data on ballistic weaponry and you'll be glad to hear that we just cracked one of their files.
By applying what we've learned to our gauss rifle design, i believe we can further increase its range and armour penetration, and perhaps even how much damage each round causes on impact.

Our sebillian "friends" have unwittingly provided us with some useful information via a file we managed to decrypt.
By using this information with our shotgun design, i believe we can increase its range and how many pellets it can fire per shot.

The information we stole from the sebillians has provided us with some ideas for upgrading our mk-2 sniper rifle.
We're replacing the barrel with a more robust design, which should help improve aiming and range.
We've also redesigned the projectile slightly to further improve its armour penetration, although this will mean a slight drop in impact damage.

With what we've learned from the sebillians during our latest hacking attempt we believe we can carry out some modifications to our gauss HMG.
If all goes to plan it should have an increased clip-size, along with increased range, damage and armour penetration.
That should cheer your men up!

A sebillian ballistics report we recently stole has provided us with some thoughts on ways to upgrade our minigun.
By increasing its power supply through the use of alenium, we can increase its range, and we've redesigned its projectile which will lead to far greater clip capacity along with increased armour penetration and hopefully allow for greater accuracy.

With what we've learned from studying alien wave technology, I believe we're close to developing a new type of energy weapon.
It will be a combination of our earlier laser and plasma technologies, but with some refinements we've gained through the study of wave weaponry.
Once complete it should provide us with weapons capable of extremely accurate and long range energy beams. The beam itself appears to be naturally armour penetrative, but will deal lower damage on impact than plasmas.

Following our studies of all alien wave technologies we believe we can make some enhancements to our pulse weaponry.
We still need to carry out some tests on how best to achieve this, but rest assured, it won't be long now.

One of the first designs we have for pulse weapons is a pistol.
It will be far easier to aim than a plasma pistol, along with having almost double the range and greatly increased charge capacity.
This combined with the armour penetration of the beam itself should make it more effective in combat than our earlier plasma pistol.

We're currently working on adapting a shotgun to use our pulse technology.
Once completed, it should be capable of very high accuracy for this type of weapon, along with increased damage over its laser version. It will still be limited to very short range though due to the power being dispersed over multiple "pellets".
They're not really pellets of course, instead we cause the pulse beam to fragment upon leaving the muzzle, which causes loss of cohesion after a short distance, thus limiting the effective range.

We have a design for a rifle based on our pulse technology.
Initial testing looks promising, showing improved accuracy and range over the plasma rifle. It can also hold far more charges per clip.
The beam itself will penetrate armour more effectively but deal less damage on impact.

We've been looking at adapting our pulse rifle into a longer range version, a sniper rifle.
Our prototype has demonstrated far greater range than its plasma counterpart along with improved accuracy. It is also extremely effective against armour.
It should also be capable of firing more shots before you need to recharge its clip.

Our initial attempts at creating a HMG that can use pulse technology met with failure, but not all is bad news.
Due to its increased size, it has a far greater charge capacity than a shotgun, so we adapted our beam splitting technique to work with this weapon with great effect.
Essentially, it splits a high-energy beam into 3 lesser beams which can maintain cohesion over a reasonable distance. The downside is that each beam requires a significant amount of charging before another can be fired, so its not a replacement for a shotgun.

By combining what we've learned during the development of precison, carbine and heavy pulse weaponry, we've come up with a design for a pulse minigun.
Our prototype has shown some remarkable results, being far more accurate than any previous minigun, and by splitting each beam in two as it leaves the muzzle, it causes an extreme amount of damage on anything unlucky enough to stray into its line of fire.
All this power comes at the cost of downtime between each burst as its capacitors recharge, so try not to miss.

We have a plan for upgrading our pulse pistol using information we've gained from further study into pulse technology.
By refining the beam, it should be capable of maintaining cohesion over longer distances, thus increasing both range and accuracy, along with requiring less charge per shot fired.
It will also penetrate armour more readily and deal slightly more damage on impact.

Using our increased understanding of pulse technology, we've come up with a few tweaks for our pulse carbine.
Once completed, it should be capable of firing bursts of 4 shots instead of 3, increasing its damage output by 33%%.

Following on from our study into more advanced aspects of pulse technology, we have some ideas which should improve the pulse rifle.
Beam refinement should double the amount of shots it can fire per clip, along with reducing the downtime between shots. It will also increase the range and accuracy of the beam along with giving it greater armour penetration and slightly improved impact damage.
We're also looking to increase the burst fire capabilities of the rifle.

Advancements in pulse technology have given us some thoughts on ways to improve the precision rifle.
The refined beam will be more accurate and capable of maintaining cohesion over longer distances while also requiring less charge per shot, thus increasing clip capacity and reducing charge time between shots.
It should also have an easier time penetrating armour and deal greater damage on impact.

We've been struggling to integrate what we've learned from advanced pulse technology into our heavy weapon.
Beam refinement will naturally lead to increased range and more shots per clip, but unfortunately, beam splitting does not lend itself to accuracy although we have made some marginal improvements there.
Our main upgrade will be splitting the beam into 4 leading to a major increase in overall damage caused.

Our research into advanced pulse technology has given us a few ideas for modifying the pulse minigun.
We can't really increase its accuracy due to how this weapon works, but refining the beam will increase its range and clip capacity.
As each beam now requires less charge per shot, we should also be able to increase the amount of shots you can fire per burst.

We've recently uncovered some new information on energy manipulation from a decrypted caesan file.
This should allow us to further refine the beam fired by our pulse pistol to achieve even longer range, higher charge capacity and perhaps even better armour penetration and damage.
We're still at the testing stage, but i'll let you know when it's ready.

I think we can finally increase the range of our pulse carbine by a massive 33%% thanks to data we stole from the Caesans.
We also have plans to increase its burst fire capability thus increasing its damage as well.

With the information we've gained from a recent hacking attempt on the caesans we believe we can carry out some modifications to our pulse rifle.
By even further refining the pulse beam, we should be able to achieve a longer range and increased accuracy, all while reducing the charge required to generate it, resulting in greater shot capacity.
It may possibly even cause more damage on impact, but we're still working on that to perfect it.

Some of the data on energy weapons which we decrypted from a caesan computer has given us a few ideas for upgrading our pulse precision rifle.
IF it was accurate before, now it should be almost impossible for your soldiers to miss their target. Also the beam refinement has led to increased range while needing less energy per shot, thus increasing clip capacity.
Finally the refined beam should be capable of even better armour penetration and damage on impact.

We've come up with some modifications for our heavy pulse weapon after reviewing some data from a caesan computer.
Not only will the refined beam have increased range while requiring less charge per beam thus increasing clip capacity, but it should be more accurate as well.
But the best part is we've devised a way to split the beam into 5, all of which will have greater armour penetration and impact damage than the previous model making this a very substantial upgrade.
Unfortunately, we're only at prototype stage currently, but we should have it ready for production soon.

The caesans had some very interesting information on energy manipulation locked away in one of those files we decrypted.
Using what we've learned, we believe we can upgrade our pulse minigun to give it a longer range, increased clip capacity, better armour penetration and even increased impact damage.
We've also come up with a method for smoothing out the spinning of the barrels which will hopefully result in increased accuracy.

Our research on alien mass weaponry has given us some ideas for a "new" type of kinetic weapon. Actually rail-guns have been around since the end of the first World War, but they've never been practical weapons due to a few limitations. Until I got involved that is!
By swapping out the rails and the armature with new ones designed and built around our knowledge of hardened alien alloys I believe we can eliminate the degradation issues caused by friction and by using alenium we should be able to reduce the overall size of the power source required to fire a projectile.
We're still working out some scaling issues, but I believe we will be able to start working on viable hand-held rail guns very shortly.

Even though our rail guns have proven to be quite effective in the field, we've come up with some theories on improving them based on our studies of advanced alien mass technology.
We still need to carry out quite a few tests to confirm these, but if it works we should be able to start work on improving our rail weaponry and perhaps even upgrade our base defences as well.

We've come up with a design for a new pistol based on our rail technology.
It should end up with slightly better range than our previous kinetic pistols, but the real improvement is in the damage it can cause to any target it hits.
Given the speed achievable, we expect the projectile to be better at penetrating armour and cause far more harm to its target.

With our pistol and rifle already proven successful we've started working on a combination of the two weapons.
By reducing the barrel length, it will unfortunately provide less acceleration to the projectile when compared to a rifle, but it's rapid fire capability should make it better in combat than a pistol.
Initial testing has demonstrated it to be over twice as effective against targets than a gauss SMG.

Longer barrel weapons are where rail guns really show their strength and i think that once we've successfully developed a rifle we should be able to create an even longer sniper version too.
During our lab tests, we've found it to be far more powerful than our previous gauss rifles, not to mention being easier to aim and capable of hitting a target at longer ranges.
This should prove to be a very useful addition to your arsenal once completed.

Rail technology is not well suited for weapons which fire multiple rounds per shot Commander.
We're currently working on a way around this and have had some success with encasing each projectile within a disposable casing which is stripped away by air friction.
It's not perfect though as the additional mass of the rounds and casing will severely limit the range of this weapon, however anything it hits will likely end up as dog meat.

A sniper rifle is perfect for rail technology due to its increased barrel length.
We have great hopes for this weapon and predict it to be far more damaging than its gaussian predecessor, not to mention being easier to aim due to how the rails operate.
In addition, the length of the barrel should allow the projectile to retain lethal velocity over quite impressive distances.

We've come up with a design for a heavy machine gun that utilises our rail technology.
I admit that it wasn't easy commander, propelling so many projectiles along a single barrel is quite detrimental to the rails themselves, but we think we've found a solution. I won't bore you with the details, but if this works it should be markedly better than our gauss HMG.

We've pooled our knowledge on rail carbines, HMG's and sniper rifles and have come up with a blueprint for a minigun.
If it works, this thing will be extremely dangerous not to mention heavy. It should probably be mounted on a vehicle as opposed to carried by a soldier, but anything it hits should be shredded to pieces almost instantly.
Of course, it's all still theory at present, but we're working on making it a reality.

We've come up with some improvements to our rail pistol and if they work out i think your troops will be well impressed.
Increased range and reduced recoil should both help with actually hitting a target, but the real magic is in the redesigned round which should be capable of penetrating most armours as well as causing more damage on impact.

Based on what we've learned from our more advanced studies on rail technology i think we can upgrade our SMG.
In the end it should have slightly increased range along with a far higher rate of fire.
This comes with a downside, each projectile, while being far better at penetrating armour will also likely cause less damage upon impact due to it's redesigned profile.
However, even though I am a genius and your troops are not, i'm sure they can appreciate that more projectiles per burst equals more damage to the target.

Our advancements in rail technology have given me a few ideas for upgrading our rifle design.
Not only do i believe i can make it more accurate, but with some work, it should also be capable of hitting a target at longer distances.
We're also redesigning the projectile to help increase its armour penetration capabilities along with impact damage.

We've come up with a few modifications to our shotgun.
By smoothing out the interaction between the rails and armature i believe we can help reduce its recoil, thus improving accuracy and we've also redesigned the projectiles slightly to allow more of them to be fired per shot.
Once everything is fully configured it should result in quite a boost to the harm this weapon can cause.

We have some plans to improve our sniper rifle with theories gained from study of the more advanced aspects of rail technology.
Once completed, it should be capable of vastly greater range and be more accurate to boot.
We're also working on a new projectile which should be capable of penetrating even the heaviest of armours and delivering more impact damage as well.

Our research into advanced rail technology has given me a few ideas for our HMG.
I believe i can increase its range by approximately 25%% and also its rate of fire. We've also redesigned the projectile itself so that it has a smaller profile, hopefully resulting in higher armour penetration and increased clip capacity.
If this works our HMG should be a lot more effective in the field.

I wasn't sure that we could improve upon our original minigun design, but with our increased understanding of rail technology it might be possible.
By making some adjustments to the timing mechanism, i believe we can increase its rate of fire and our new rounds should also prove more damaging to anything it hits.
Once complete, i expect this version to outperform our original by approximately 50%%.

With some information we've recently discovered from sebillian reports on ballistics we might be able to upgrade our mk-2 pistol.
We believe it will result in increased range and damage per projectile, but still need to carry out comprehensive testing on it to make sure.

The sebillains had some ballistic reports hidden on a flie we recently decrypted. They may prove useful in other areas, but have initially given us some ideas for improving our rail SMG.
If these reports are accurate, we should be able to improve its range, rate of fire and damage per round.
Naturally this is still in the testing phase, but we hope to have it ready for production soon.

Our rail rifles are pretty lethal as they are, but we've come across some interesting information through hacking sebillian files.
If correct, i believe we can greatly increase the accuracy and range of our rifle along with a modest increase in both armour penetration and impact damage.

The sebillians had a report on advanced acceleration techniques used in their ballistic weaponry locked away on one of their computers. We've managed to unlock it and think it might be useful for upgrading our carbine.
If the data in the report is accurate we believe we can not only increase the maximum range of our carbine, but also the amount of projectiles which can be fired with one shot, thus leading to a nice increase in damage as well.

You'll be amazed with the modifications we've come up with for our sniper rifle, all thanks to some data we stole from the sebillians.
Not only can we increase it's range, but new sighting techniques and error correction should make it almost impossible to miss a target, unless your soldiers fire with their eyes closed.
We're also redesigning the projectile to achieve maximum armour penetration along with improved impact damage.

Based on data hacked from a sebillian databank we've come up with some small, but significant changes for our HMG.
Once completed, we hope to achieve greater range and accuracy along with a slight increase in impact damage and armour penetration.
We also believe that the modified projectiles should allow us to fit more of them into a clip, thus reducing the need for reloading.

We've come up with some interesting theories for modifying our minigun thanks to some data obtained from the sebillians.
If they work, we think we can not only increase its range and accuracy but also its rate of fire.
We're also working on redesigning the projectile to allow more per clip along with increased armour penetration and possibly higher impact damage.
I've also taken the liberty of patenting this design for use with aircraft and vehicles as its weight makes it more suited for those applications.

With our studies of ion technology complete we have come up with an idea for a new type of energy weapon. It's actually only very loosely based on ion technology, but we did get a few of the key principles from there.
By emitting an energy beam which causes the molecules of its target to vibrate we believe we can achieve an extremely effective energy weapon against any organic lifeform.
Unfortunately, this beam tends to be deflected almost completely by armour so we're still looking on ways to improve it.
I believe that with a little more research and testing we should be able to weaponise it very soon.

We've come up with some new theories based on our research into sonic weapons and also the more advanced alien ion weaponry.
If correct we believe we can further increase the damage caused by modulating the frequency of the beam as it hits the target, causing even more vibration and literally ripping the target apart from the inside.
We still need to optimise this modulation as not all frequencies achieve the desired affect, but we're getting close to perfecting it.

We have a design for a pistol based on our new sonic technology.
Sonic Technology works very differently to pulse technology, so expect some major changes once completed, but to give you some idea, expect it to have shorter range, reduced charge capacity and longer charge time between shots. Doesn't sound great does it Commander?
The beauty of this weapon is that it should cause approximately triple! the damage of a pulse pistol against any soft target.

This new rifle is based on our sonic technology and because of that comes with some disadvantages when compared to our pulse rifles.
Put simply, it cannot achieve the same maximum range and takes longer to fire between shots along with the extra charge involved per shot reducing clip capacity.
But none of that compares to the massive increase in damage it will cause to any non-armoured target that it hits.

Now that we've successfully developed a sonic rifle, we've started looking into its applications in precision rifles.
The damage it can cause is really quite impressive Commander, but it does have all the downsides associated with our rifle and pistol weapons such as reduced range, clip size and increased charging time between shots when compared to a pulse precision rifle.
I firmly believe that the benefits outweigh the downsides as on average each beam will be 300%% more damaging.

Coming up with a design for a cannon-type weapon based on sonic technology was quite the challenge, but by pooling everything we've learned from the invention of our other sonic weapons, we've finally come up with a viable weapon.
It will be a relatively short range weapon for it's class and each shot will fully deplete it's clip capacitors, but the beam itself will be devastating to anything it hits and also have a similar effect to anything close to the point of impact.

With our research on assault rifles utilising sonic technology completed, we're now trying to adapt it to a HMG design.
We've had some success and initial data suggests that it will be considerably more powerful than its pulse equivalent with estimates ranging as high as a 400%% increase in damage.
It will have reduced range and require reloading quite often, but with it's increased damage i'm sure your troops won't complain ... well, not any more than usual anyway.

Our research into the more advanced aspects of sonic technology have given us some ideas for upgrading our pistol design.
We can't really improve its range with our current technology but by modulating the beam frequency we believe we can increase the damage it causes upon impact.
We're also looking at making some modifications to the charging process which should help to reduce the downtime between shots.

We've come up with some upgrades for our sonic rifle based on new theories on sonic technology.
If correct, we believe we can reduce the charging time between shots along with increasing the damage each beam causes to its target. It still won't be very effective against armour so choose your targets well.

Our research into advanced applications of sonics has led to some ideas for improving our precision rifle.
I believe that we can not only increase the damage each beam causes, but also reduce the charge time between each shot fired.
We're also working on smoothing out the firing action which should help make the beam more accurate.

Now that we have more detailed knowledge on how sonic technology works with weapons, we've come up with some improvements for our sonic cannon.
The smallest of these changes should result in increased range, but that's not all we have planned.
Our modulated beam should cause approximately 50%% more damage along with reducing the charge required per shot, thereby increasing its rate of fire along with smoothing out the firing action making it easier to aim.
I'm sure your men will be quite impressed with the end result.

Our increased understanding of sonic technology has given me some ideas for our HMG.
I don't believe we can increase its range or rate of fire, but we can smooth out its firing action to make it slightly easier to aim. We're also working on integrating our modulated frequency beam into this design which will result in increased damage to the target.

Thanks to data uncovered from a caesan computer, we've come up with some serious upgrades for our sonic pistol.
If everything goes according to plan, we should be able to increase its range quite significantly along with the damage it causes to any target it hits.

We've uncovered information on energy beams from a caesan file which may allow us to improve our sonic rifle.
If correct, we should be able to increase both its range and damage due to some refinements to the beam.
I doubt we'll be able to increase the effectiveness of this weapon any further with our current technology Commander.

Those Caesans had some very interesting data on energy weapons stored in a file which we've recently managed to crack.
If what they say is true, then we might be able to improve our precision sonic rifle quite significantly, most notably it's range and the damage the beam can cause to a target.
I'm sure your troops will appreciate being able to successfully shoot at the aliens from further away.

Our recent hacking attempt on a Caesan computer has struck gold commander.
If the data we've managed to extract is accurate we may be able to improve both the range and impact damage of the beam fired by our sonic cannon.
Once again, i suggest you remind your men not to fire this weapon in close quarters, it will easily kill your trooper if fired at an adjacent alien.

We've recently had a stroke of luck Commander. One of those files we managed to decrypt was a caesan report on applications of energy in rapid-fire weaponry.
This has obvious theoretical benefits to our sonic HMG which we're currently working on making a reality.
Once completed I expect it to have an increased range along with each beam being capable of inflicting more harm to its target.

The alien rebel has proven quite informative commander.
We had him watch our recent interrogation of that terror attack operative from hiding.
He believes that some of the information divulged by the captive may be of use in developing anti-matter weaponry.

I think that by combining what we've learned from the alien dark technology with our existing theorems on anti-matter technology we'll be able to further our understanding of both fields.
Hopefully this will lead to innovations for our existing anti-matter weaponry, potentially leading to anti-matter particles with an increased yield on annihilation.

By combining what we already know about anti-matter technology with what we've recently learned about alien advanced dark weaponry, i believe we can make some advancements in the field of anti-matter technology.
If our theories prove to be correct we should be able to upgrade our existing anti-matter weaponry significantly.

We came upon some interesting information during our recent interrogation of one of the aliens controlling their terror attacks. By combining this with what we already know about anti-matter and alien ancient technology i believe we can further our own understanding of anti-matter and its applications in weaponry.
We still have a lot of work to do, but if correct we hope to be able to start improving our own anti-matter arsenal once completed.

Yes Commander it's a pistol and no you cannot fire it in here.
It's a prototype of our new anti-matter weaponry which is presenting us with some problems.
When anti-matter meets matter such as the air for example, it reacts violently. we need to iron this out so that the reaction will only occur upon impact with a target.

This is a longer barrel version of our pistol prototype, which unfortunately faces the same issues.
The reaction is even more violent in this case and caused the original model to explode upon firing. Not exactly useful in the field unless you get the enemy to fire it for you.
We'll work on it commander, i'm confident we're close to making this a viable weapon.

Now that we've successfully deployed a working version of our anti-matter rifle, I think we can attempt a sniper version of the same.
The higher velocity of the rounds may cause some friction issues so we'll need to carry out extensive testing on it to ensure your troops safety.

We're applying some of the energy manipulation data we pulled from the caesan archives to our cannon design along with some principles discovered during the creation of the sniper rifle.
If this works we'll have a weapon capable of spitting out tremendous amounts of high-speed anti-matter filled projectiles.
I suggest you be extremely careful where you point it Commander.

We've taken a rifle and modified it to accept a larger calibre round. In theory this will result in quite impressive damage to whatever it manages to hit.
It still needs some tweaking though, our test targets are still on fire from an earlier experiment.

With our new positron anti-matter particles we have been able to come up with a new design for our anti-matter pistols.
With new casings designed specifically for this particle, we can fire them further before annihilation thus increasing our range, and the particle itself has almost double the yield of our original anti-matter particles.
Some design considerations need to be cleared first, you really don't want one of these rounds detonating by accident.

We have plans for an upgraded version of our mk-1 rifle.
Most of the proposed changes are required in order to facilitate the rounds containing our new anti-matter particle, but we've also modified the firing mechanism which should increase it's range slightly.

With the successful development of our mk-2 rifle, it's time to apply the same upgrades to our sniper rifles.
As with the rifle, expect increased damage and range once we're finished. It will still be a single shot rifle as these rounds are too volatile to bunch together in a clip, but that shot will pack a punch.

After the upgrades we've carried out on all our other mk-1 anti-matter weapons we turned our attention to our minigun design.
Unfortunately, making the same type of upgrade to it confounded us, even me! Until yesterday that is.
We unlocked some files on Caesan caelium studies and believe we can use those to increase the already impressive damage caused by our existing minigun.
This still needs some work to get right, but should increase it's range, damage and armour penetration when completed.

Following analysis of field reports regarding the mk-2 rifle, we've made some revisions to the design of the mk-1 cannon.
We've modified the round to accept our new anti-matter particle and also added a proximity sensor to it which will cause it to release the anti-matter microseconds before impact.
This will substantially increase the area of annihilation resulting in greater damage to the area around the target.
We still need to fine-tune the sensors to achieve optimum release timing, but expect to have them perfected shortly.

With our research into advanced anti-matter theories completed, we can now look at upgrading our weapons.
To start with we have plans to modify the pistol design in order to achieve a greater range.
We're also redesigning the shell containing the anti-matter particle to achieve greater armour penetration and damage

Now that we have a better understanding of anti-matter and created a new element for its use we can look at upgrading our rifles.
If this works, the rifle should have increased range, and the projectile will cause substantially more damage while also being better at penetrating armour.

With our new anti-matter rifle design being a success, we've turned our sights on a sniper rifle ... stop groaning!
Very well, no more jokes. We believe we can increase the range, damage and armour penetration of the sniper rifle although it still requires some further testing before you can start production.

With our sniper and cannons already upgraded we turned our attention to the minigun design and thankfully had a bit of luck with some of the data we pulled from caesan computers.
Once completed, this will be an extremely dangerous weapon, with increased range, damage and armour penetration over its mk-2 predecessor.
Unfortunately, it's quite heavy and should probably be mounted on a tank instead of being carried by a soldier.

Now that we have a working MK-3 anti-matter rifle we can look to upgrading our cannon design as well.
If all goes to plan, it should also be capable of firing over an increased distance, while delivering far more damage upon detonation.
We're trying to increase the armour penetration of the round as well, but this will likely mean the blast radius stays the same as before, even though it's a more powerful blast.

With our research into ancient anti-matter technology completed i believe we can work on upgrading our pistol design.
This should result in a slight increase in range, but the real benefit will be the new anti-matter particle used, which will deliver far more damage to whatever it comes into contact with, including armour plating.

This new rifle design is based on our studies of ancient anti-matter technology.
Once completed it should be capable of firing the projectile over a longer range along with causing vastly increased damage to the target due to the reaction of our new particle.
Our current data from testing has shown it to be over 50%% more effective against any target.

With the design of our anti-matter rifle completed we now feel confident of achieving the same effects with a sniper rifle.
I have no doubt that this will be successful and fully expect it to be capable of firing projectiles over an increased distance and causing massive devastation to any target it hits, armoured or not.
It will still be a single shot weapon and each round is quite weighty so try not to miss.

This will be our ultimate anti-matter weapon and is based on everything we've learned from previous designs.
Once completed, it should have increased range along with substantially increased damage to all targets it hits.
The annihilation of the particle should make most armours completely irrelevant thus causing maximum damage to anything it hits.

With our rifle upgrade completed we've turned to upgrading our cannon weapon.
As you know, this weapon is more useful for area effect damage due to the sensors in the round which cause detonation just before impact. Once our upgrades are completed i believe the new particle will cause substantially more damage to a wider area and we also believe we can increase the effective range of the weapon.
I would suggest you tell your men to be careful where they fire it, it is not ideal for close quarters and is also responsible for our new doorway in what was a 3 foot thick reinforced concrete wall.

Now that we've completed our studies on wave pistols and rifles, along with what we've learned from the caesan warriors who carry them, we can start to work on how they operate.
Initial testing has indicated they form a type of energy wave, which we may be capable of emulating to improve our own energy and shock weaponry.
If this research proves successful it will herald a new era of energy weapons for humankind ... along with some increased recognition for my work among the scientific community.

Our recent interrogation of a caesan weapons Commander has led to some interesting developments in understanding alien wave technology.
There are quite a few small but important similarities between alien photon technology and their more advanced wave weaponry.
I believe that a closer examination of these will help us more fully understand how wave technology works and thus enable us to further improve our own energy based weapons.
