This is a new type of energy weapon that the caesan have started carrying into battle.
Preliminary reports indicate that it's more powerful than their plasma pistol, but further testing will be required to determine how it functions.

A slightly larger and more powerful version of the wave pistol, but still sharing many of its characteristics.
Study of this may shed some new light on how wave technology operates.

This appears to be the rifle version of their wave technology.
Study of this should definitely help us in understanding wave technology and perhaps find a way to utilise it.

This is a long-range energy weapon utilising wave technology.
It's more advanced design suggests refinements over that evident in the basic weapons, so an examination of its construction may help us develop new theories which could improve our understanding of wave technology.

The HMG of the alien wave technology based arsenal.
It's construction seems far more advanced than that of the rifle and may help us to discover more about wave technology and its uses.

This is a dangerous weapon Commander. Not only does it cause damage to whatever target it hits, its delivery is powerful enough to also impact on nearby targets as well.
The good news is that with some additional examination of it, we may be able to use it to increase our knowledge of alien wave technology.

This appears to be a slightly improved version of the alien wave rifle. The upgrades, while small, reveal some quite intriguing details about how wave technology functions.
Additional analysis of these differences in design might enable us to more fully understand how this technology generates these waves.

Following our examination of the latest alien pistols and rifles, we've come up with some theories as to how they operate.
I don't think we can replicate this design, but certain aspects of it are intriguing and have given me some ideas for possibly improving our MAG Weaponry.
I'm going to question that Sebillian Warrior you captured again, to see if I can get anything more out of him.

We're getting close to more fully understanding these new vindicator weapons the aliens are using.
Our interrogation of the Sebillian Weapons Commander has led us to drawing comparisons between their scorcher technology and their more advanced vindicator weaponry.
Completion of this project will hopefully increase our understanding of their kinetic type weapons in general, and thus give us ideas for improving our own such weaponry.

This appears to be a slightly more advanced version of their Matergy sidearms.
Further study will be required to make any use of whatever they've done to improve it.

It's an upgraded version of their Matergy weapons Commander.
We'll examine it further to see if we can determine how this was achieved and begin to understand this new technology.

Hmm, a more powerful version of their Matergy sniper rifles. I'd suggest trying not to wander into its line-of-sight Commander.
We'll need to study it more closely which might lead to a better understanding of their vindicator weaponry.

This new HMG appears to have a greatly increased clip size compared to it's predecessor along with increased damage.
If we study this, we may be able to discover how they achieved this and apply it to our own weaponry in the future.

This is an extremely dangerous weapon Commander, try to make killing anything holding one a priority.
It appears to have increased range, damage and rate of fire over its matergy counterpart, but we still need to carry out more tests on it to determine how this was made possible.

A very powerful single-shot, high-impact weapon utilising their vindicator technology.
Further study of this may provide us with what we're missing to complete our understanding of these types of weaponry and thereby improve our own weapons.

Based on our studies of their pistol and rifle variants of scorcher technology, along with what we extracted from a sebillian weapons commander, we've come up with some working theories on how this technology functions.
I won't bore you with the details Commander, but initial studies have shown these weapons to be almost twice as powerful as their flamer predecessors.
Understanding exactly how they've achieved this should also help us with some issues we've been trying to solve with their vindicator technology.

Following our studies of their more advanced scorcher weaponry, we're beginning to more completely understand how these weapons function.
A more detailed inspection of certain aspects of them along with what we've recently learned from our interrogation of a sebillian weapons commander should help unveil the last of their secrets.
XXDescriptionXX

These new weapons seem to have been designed to replace their flamer versions. Initial studies of this pistol have indicated it's almost twice as powerful as its predecessor.
We'll need to study it further to discover how they've managed to achieve this.

This rifle appears to cause almost double the damage of its flamer version.
With some more analysis we may be able to determine how this is possible.

This is a rapid-fire version of their scorcher weaponry Commander. As with all other Scorcher weapons, it appears to be almost twice as powerful as the flamers they've replaced.
Further examination of this will be required if we ever wish to fully understand how this technology works.

The heavy hitter of their scorcher technology. Initial testing has shown that it has the capacity to inflict damage on a wide area around its point of impact, so be careful.
With a little more study we may be able to uncover how this was achieved and update our information on scorcher technology in general.

This "blood" technology is extremely dangerous Commander. Following our initial tests on blood pistols and rifles we were still a little in the dark as to its composition.
We tested it on an alien terror captive and found to our surprise that its a chemical weapon equally effective against all organic lifeforms, including the aliens.
Why they would introduce something like this in a battle where it can easily kill them as well is beyond us, but further testing will hopefully reveal its chemical composition to us and potentially lead to improvements in our own chemical weaponry.

Blood technology is well suited for terror missions given its nature and appears to be where it occurs the most often.
We're in the process of carrying out further investigations on the heavy weapons which fire it and questioning the operator captured from one such terror mission about its origins.
Hopefully these elements combined will lead us to more fully understand it and find ways to counter it.
XXDescriptionXX

An insidious weapon capable of firing a chemical compound at its target.
We'll need to study this if we ever wish to come up with countermeasures to combat it.

A larger version of the pistol, capable of longer range.
We don't know enough about this "blood" yet to be able to do much with or about it, but further analysis should help rectify that.

A weapon capable of firing rapid volleys of blood at its target, which makes it extremely devastating during terror attacks on our densely populated cities.
Close examination of how this weapon works may deepen our understanding of this threat.

Due to the splash damage its projectile is capable of inflicting on impact, this is an especially dangerous weapon in congested areas.
Further study of this weapon might help us increase our knowledge of blood technology as a whole.

Photon technology appears to be a direct successor to their earlier neutron technology.
We still don't know exactly how it works and will need to study their rapid-fire photon weapons a little more to discern this, but we have a promising lead following the interrogation of a caesan weapons commander.
We're hopeful that upon completion, we'll be able to use this knowledge to advance our understanding of alien energy technology.

Our interrogation of a caesan weapons commander and the information we extracted from him, combined with our study of alien photon technology and now its long range weaponry has provided some quite useful insights into how it generates its energy beam.
Further analysis is still needed to completely comprehend this technology, but we hope to have that completed shortly.
XXDescriptionXX

A typical alien rifle design, but one capable of firing this new photon energy they've developed.
A comprehensive examination of its parts should enable us to come up with theories on how this energy is generated.

A long-range weapon capable of firing photon beams at its target.
Further study of this should enable us to enhance our knowledge of photon technology and its uses.

A truly devastating weapon if taken unawares, especially as it uses their new photon technology, but thankfully it takes a long time to reload.
I believe that with some further analysis of this weapon we may discover the secret of photon technology ourselves.

Be careful around this weapon in enclosed spaces commander, it can cause damage to the area around the beams point of impact.
By studying how it achieves this, we should gain a far greater understanding of photon technology in general.

Our initial analysis of alien ion pistols and rifles along with the interrogation of a high-ranking caesan soldier have led to some worrying theories.
To put it simply, this new ion technology appears to be based on our own laser and plasma technologies only they've improved on them both significantly. While its flattering to know that the aliens have found one of my designs to be worthy of emulating, the modifications they've made are still baffling.
We need to research this further to see if we can extract anything of use from it and perhaps upgrade our own energy based weapons.

From our studies of alien ion and thunder technology along with some unusual characteristics exhibited by the more advanced ion weaponry, we've come up with some theories which may lead to more fully understanding how this technology operates.
We've also been questioning a Caesan Tactical Commander about the purpose and goals the aliens use these weapons for along with trying to extract as much technical data as possible about them from him.
Once this study is complete, we hope to be able to apply any new principles we learn to upgrading our own beam weaponry.

Initial testing of this weapon has shown it to be capable of higher energy output over a longer range than any of their preceding energy pistols.
We'll need to take it apart and study it further if we wish to understand how they've achieved this.

As with its little brother the ion pistol, they have upgraded these weapons to make them even more deadly than the earlier wave type technologies.
After we've dismantled it and discovered the source of these improvements we should be able to start generating theories on how it was achieved and perhaps find ways to utilise these modifications ourselves.

This weapon appears to be capable of hitting a target at extreme distances with a high rate of accuracy. I suggest you find cover when facing an alien equipped with one.
After we take it apart we hope to be able to discover exactly how they've achieved all of these improvements over their earlier beam weapons.

They've adapted their ion technology into a rapid-fire weapon. It appears to have a slightly reduced maximum range in comparison to their wave version, but at close range the increased rate-of-fire and damage per beam will be quite lethal.
We need to discover how they've achieved these upgrades and will start working on it as soon as possible.

This new cannon type weapon is considerably more dangerous than its wave predecessor. It's capable of a higher maximum range, along with increased damage per beam, but the worst part is that the charging mechanism for the beam has been significantly altered allowing it to fire almost twice as fast.
We really need to understand how they've achieved this feat and with a little luck we'll be able to use that information to improve our own energy weapons.

Our interrogation of a high-ranking sebillian warrior along with our studies of their mass pistols and rifles has led us to surmise that these weapons were initially designed for use in low-gravity environments, very similar to our own mass-driver theories which is what we've named these weapons after.
While we can't create mass-drivers which would operate efficiently in our atmosphere, the construction methodology and power supply of these weapons may prove useful for providing some new insights into kinetic weaponry which we can use.
I'm afraid it will take some more time to ascertain if this will work or not Commander, but I'm hopeful that it will enable us to develop new weaponry based on it once completed.

After our interrogation of that Sebillian Tactical Commander, I took some time to go over all the notes we've taken regarding their basic and advanced mass weaponry along with certain aspects of their incinerator technology and come up with some theories about how they work in our atmosphere.
If correct, this should allow us to gain a deeper understanding of this technology and perhaps find ways to apply this to our own kinetic weaponry branches to improve them.

While this new pistol doesn't exhibit any huge improvements over its vindicator rival, the fact that it can operate in earth-gravity conditions at all is remarkable.
Further study of this should allow us to start to understand how this is possible.

Like its smaller cousin, the pistol, the fact that this weapon works here at all is amazing. I think it has something to do with the smaller profile of the projectiles along with a vastly increased power supply or propulsion system but we'll need to study it further to ascertain how exactly they've achieved this.
Even though the projectiles are smaller, they're capable of inflicting greater damage per round than those found in the vindicators ... baffling!

A highly accurate long-range version of their mass weapons. The projectiles in this are actually slightly larger than those found in vindicators, but the increased power supply enables the gun to fire them at comparable speeds. This has resulted in them causing more impact damage and penetrating armour plating a little more easily.
We need to understand how they've achieved this if we wish to develop working theories on how we can do the same for our own weapons.

A burst-fire variant on their mass technology. As with all other types of this technology that we've recovered, it appears to be capable of causing higher damage per projectile fired.
One notable difference is that this particular weapon appears to be quite inaccurate at long ranges. Perhaps once we've taken it apart we can discover why this is so.

You really don't want to ever be facing down the barrels of one of these Commander. Its improved damage over the vindicator version will almost certainly spell doom for anyone in such a position.
Hopefully by taking it apart and studying its internal mechanisms we can gain a greater understanding of how this technology operates.

One of their more advanced mass weapons, this time a cannon design. The amount of power needed to propel the larger projectile is really quite staggering.
Further study of its internal workings will hopefully reveal to us how they managed to achieve this.

The alien incinerators we've studied to date such as the pistol and rifle variant seem to be more an upgrade to their scorcher technology rather than a completely new weapons branch. Information we've extracted from a captive sebillian tactical commander would appear to confirm that this is the case also.
They now fire bolts of super-heated magma which is encased in a plasma shell as it leaves the barrel to help maintain its cohesion over distance. This shell then dissolves on impact with any solid matter allowing the magma to do its deadly work.
Further study may reveal to us exactly how this process is achieved and might lead to some new developments for our own weaponry.

These new weapons bear some remarkable similarities to their earlier scorcher models, but have a longer range and deal out higher damage upon impact.
With a little study we should be able to figure out how these increases were made and potentially find ways to utilise them ourselves.

Similar to its smaller cousin the pistol, the main improvements to this weapon appear to be in increased range and impact damage.
I'm sure that with further study we'll be able to unravel its secrets.

It's appears to essentially be a heavy machine gun type weapon which spits bolts of magma instead of standard projectiles. Extremely dangerous should you get caught by a salvo of rounds.
Hopefully by taking it apart we'll discover how they can sustain this rate of fire.

A very dangerous adaptation of incinerator technology, not so much in the damage caused by the initial impact, but more the almost certain chance of it setting afire to anything in a wide area around it.
We'll learn more about it's capabilities after we've had some time to study its construction and internal parts.

Going by what we've discovered about hybrid pistols and rifles along with data amassed from observing the reactions of various alien terrorists and professors when confronted with these weapons we've come up with some disturbing theories.
Their original toxin and blood weaponry had apparently been in use for some time prior to their invasion here. However, this hybrid technology is brand new. The weapon itself appears to have been adapted from their latest kinetic weaponry to provide an improved delivery system, while the toxin itself was engineered specifically for dealing with us.
The only piece of good news in all of this is that the new toxin is equally effective against the aliens which we may be able to turn to our advantage with some further study.

This weapon looks like its almost brand new. Interesting.
Initial testing indicates that its capable of longer range than previous biological pistols, while the actual toxin itself seems to be far more dangerous. Further testing will hopefully reveal what they've done to manage this.

This rifle appears to fire rounds containing the same toxin as that found in their pistol weapons and the rifle itself has been modified to enable it to be fired at a target from further away.
I think the aliens themselves are scared of the toxin contained in the round but we will require further testing to determine if this is true or not.

This rifle is capable of firing their new toxin at quite distant targets, but thankfully it is fairly slow to fire due to the pressures involved.
We need to study more of this new toxin to fully understand its chemical structure and perhaps be able to modify it to our own designs in the future.

A very dangerous weapon to face in confined spaces due to the nature of the round it fires.
Rather than a bullet, think of it as a miniature explosive or rocket.
Upon impact, it detonates causing damage not only to its point of impact, but also to a wide area around it.
With some further study we may find a way to utilise this concept in our own weaponry.

Following our research into alien thunder pistols and rifles along with technical information on them extracted from a caesan tactical commander we're starting to work on developing a theory as to how they generate so much power.
Not only are they effective against human targets, but they also deliver enough current to overload most circuitry they hit as well and even if the initial strike doesn't kill a human, it deals enough of a shock to temporarily incapacitate them as well.
The only good news is that armour seems to be very effective at grounding the worst of the current thus reducing the damage incurred.
Further study may help us to uncover some of the higher-level principles of their energy weapon designs.

This appears to be a vastly superior version of the aliens earlier lightning models.
Not only is it capable of causing increased stun and emp damage, but the current delivered to the point of impact is now hovering on the lethal range as well, potentially resulting in severe burns or even death.
Further study of this may provide us with some theories on how it generates this charge.

This upgrade to their lightning rifle design is really quite impressive commander.
We need to study it further if we wish to discover how they have managed to make it so much more lethal.

This is an extremely lethal weapon if you find yourself facing one at close range. A full clip will likely destroy any ground unit we have, regardless of its armouring.
Thankfully, it runs out of charge quite quickly and takes a while to reload along with being quite inaccurate at medium to long ranges so use these factors to your advantage.
With further study we may discover ways to integrate some aspects of its design into our own energy theories.

This weapon is capable of delivering a current to a wide area around the target its aimed at. We're actually not 100%% sure how this is possible and will need to carry out further research on it to resolve this.
Due to the area effect nature of this weapon, I suggest you not cluster your units in close formations when facing aliens equipped with this weapon.

While we've studied alien dark energy pistols, assault rifles and cannons, we still don't know a lot about it.
What we do know is that they somehow convert an element named Caelium into a form of anti-energy which quite literally burns through armour.
I've gone back over notes we've taken questioning various aliens we've captured during terror attacks and have come up with a theory on how this works, but i'll need more time to prove it.
Even my genius has it's limits commander!

We've now studied every type of dark energy weapon the aliens possess according to our interrogations of high-level terror operators and troops.
With this in mind, we'll need to compare all the notes we've collated about each and every one of these weapons and their effects and hopefully arrive at a deeper understanding of how they work and their actual function in this war.
Considering the principles involved with dark energy, it may lead to new theories we can use for our anti-matter weaponry.

These mysterious weapons appear to make use of an element unknown to us.
Whatever it is, it treats armour as if it wasn't there so be careful when facing one.
Further study might allow us to understand how it's created.

This appears to be a very effective anti-energy weapon which burns right through armour.
Further study is essential on these types of weapon if we ever wish to understand how they work.

It's a shame that we have no way to store or create Caelium as these rifles would likely prove quite effective against both androns and alien mechs.
Still, study of the ones you return to us might enable us to do just that in the future.

We've been studying the energy focusing arrays in this weapon in the hopes of improving our own anti-matter weaponry.
We don't have quite enough information on them yet to achieve this, but we're getting closer.

While we'd noted the armour piercing capabilities of its smaller anti-energy cousins, we had missed out on the fact that they also emit extreme amounts of electromagnetic radiation in the form of a pulse on impact.
Taking these two characteristics together, I'm beginning to believe that these were created for combat against armoured vehicles instead of personnel.
Further analysis should confirm if this is the case or not.

Be especially wary while facing someone armed with one of these, testing shows that it can disable a vehicle in seconds.
With further testing we're hopeful that we'll be able to come up with our own alternatives to this type of weapon in the near future.

We've now finished research into certain of the alien ancient weapons along with questioned the elite terror troops who used them in battle and come to a startling conclusion.
This is not an upgraded or modified design of their existing weaponry, it instead appears to originate from some extinct or forgotten source. The reason that these weapons look so dated when compared to the new models other aliens use in battle is because they are, by aeons if our calculations are correct.
We have absolutely no hope of recreating weapons like them and in fact, interrogations have revealed that neither do the aliens, but we might be able to apply some of their principles to our larger weapons or vehicles with some further study.

With our almost exhaustive research into ancient weapons complete and what we already know about them from questioning alien elite terror units we've come up with a few theories as to how they operate.
We still can't create one of our own, but under interrogation an alien praetor has admitted that the ability to create more of them has also been lost by the aliens so they are a precious and finite resource to them. However, we think that some of what we've learned might be of use in our most advanced technologies such as anti-matter research or perhaps even more advanced vehicles.
It will still take some time to nail down what applications we can make use of it in unfortunately, but we're nearly there.

This weapon is old, very old. From some things that Paul has said, i believe they may belong to a weapon-type no longer in use by the aliens normally.
That's something to be thankful for as the energy beam they emit is far stronger than any of their other energy based weapons.
It's loosely based on a bull-pup rifle design and perhaps with some further study we'll discover a way to harness this power ourselves.

Another of their ancient energy weapons, this time a long-range single shot variant.
As with the pistol, initial testing shows it to be more powerful than any of their energy based weapon equivalents.
With some further study we may be able to find a way to utilise this new form of energy.

While different in design to the ancient defender weapon, it appears to be almost identical in function, being essentially a short range assault rifle.
The real difference lies in the beam it generates as this one seems to deal primarily chemical damage to anything it contacts, extremely effective against organic lifeforms, but less of a threat to our vehicles.
Hopefully with some in-depth analysis of how this beam is generated, we'll be able to understand this technology and maybe even emulate it.

This long range version of their ancient weaponry actually fires a beam capable of causing chemical damage to anything it comes into contact with.
We'll need to study this further to understand it as currently we have no idea how its possible to achieve that effect using what still appears to be an energy beam. Knowledge such as this may become useful for development of our own technologies.

These ancient weapons are truly remarkable. Although similar in size and function to some of the other rifle variants, this particular weapon fires a beam which causes incendiary damage to it's target.
This isn't quite as baffling as the chemical variant as energy beams do tend to generate excess heat, but it's still a surprising application of it which we'd like to study further to gain a better understanding of how it's focused.

This is a long range version of the ancient horror rifle and like its smaller cousin also fires an energy beam which imparts thermal or incendiary damage to whatever it comes into contact with.
Perhaps by studying the internal mechanisms of this weapon we'll finally be able to understand how these weapons operate.

This might come as a bit of a shock to you commander, but we actually gained quite a bit of useful knowledge from the recent interrogation of an alien engineer.
One such piece was in relation to how they conduct electrical signals through their circuitry.
If we devote some time to expanding upon this principle I believe we can develop weaponry that will be highly effective against anything they possess which contains some form of electrical circuitry, while also being able to stun or otherwise incapacitate organic targets.
While we already have a basic understanding of shock technology, further study in this field could very well lead to the development of more powerful shock weaponry.

It's been simply electrifying working on a project ... oh very well, stop groaning and i promise there will be no more puns in this presentation.
We've developed a design for a pistol capable of emitting a concentrated stream of electrical energy into a nearby target.
It's range will be limited by the size of the capacitors we can fit into the housing, but shouldn't be much different from a standard pistols.
It should be capable of causing serious damage to any electrical circuitry it hits, or temporary paralysis in an organic target.

Your troops have as bad a taste in puns as my techs. They recently approached us and requested if we could integrate our shock technology into a shotgun design. They even proposed a nickname for it, the ... wait for it ... shockgun. My, how we laughed.
All that aside, with recent advancements in our shock technology I believe it might actually be possible to achieve this, but be warned that the range of such a weapon will be severely limited, although extremely powerful.
Also of note is that generating such a large charge will mean a longer waiting time between shots.

We've applied our shock technology to a standard rifle design and come up with this prototype.
It outdoes the pistol in all aspects but it manages this due to it's size, which has the drawback of making it unsuitable for a secondary weapon.
We've almost finished testing of it and I'll let you know when it's ready for use in the field.

Along with the shockgun, our advancements in shock technology have allowed us to look at integrating it into a cannon type weapon as well.
While it won't be able to do quite as much electrical damage as the shockgun, it should be able to do it from a relatively safe distance.
Remember commander, electrical circuitry tends to explode when overloaded, so it's not always a good idea to do so from close range.

Following a recent interrogation of an alien chief engineer, we're working on developing a new technology based on the manipulation of electrons.
Study of large alien computers along with andron terminals gave us some initial ideas, but it was our research into alien wave technology that really got things to this stage.
If we can make it work, we should be able to design weapons which will be extremely effective against anything which contains electrical circuitry, such as androns or alien mechs.
The discharge will also likely cause paralysis in any organic target it hits.

Further to our research into advanced alien wave weapons along with their large computers and what we've learned from disassembly of an andron terminal we've come up with some ideas for creating advanced electron weaponry.
I need to confirm some of what we've gleaned by talking to that alien chief engineer you captured again, but based on what we already know about advanced shock weaponry, it should be possible.

Our new electron technology should make the destruction of alien mechs much easier.
We're starting with a pistol design, which while it will have slightly shorter range than the earlier shock version, should be able to deliver over double the damage per shot.
While this is primarily designed for use on targets containing electronics, the surge should also prove effective at incapacitating organics.

Now that we understand it, we've decided to look at making a rifle based on electron technology.
It's range will be the same as that of the shock rifle, but the damage it causes will be substantially improved against both circuitry or organics.

Our studies into advanced electron principles has led to some interesting developments, one of which is this design for an electron sniper rifle.
It's range is unparalleled among all shock and electron weapons, while the damage reports from testing are equally impressive.
The only downside is that it requires significant recharging between each shot, so make each one count.

Now that we've completed our research into adapting electron technology to our more advanced weapons, we've come up with a design for an Electron cannon.
This will essentially be a complete overhaul of our earlier shock cannon, and testing to date indicates it will be capable of far higher damage over an increased radius from the point of impact.
Just be careful if using it on organics, as it's blast radius may cause nearby machinery to explode as well.

Our study of an alien scorcher cannon has given me some ideas for upgrading our current flamethrowers.
I think that by combining what we've learned from the alien versions with our own plasma technology, we'll be able to invent a weapon capable of matching the aliens advancements in this field.

With our increased knowledge of incendiary devices we believe we can create one small enough to be thrown at your enemies.
we'll shape it like a grenade so as to not overly confuse your troops and i'm pretty sure they know what to do with grenades.
the shell will be filled with a volatile napalm-like mixture which will likely cause small fires and severe burns on anything it touches upon exploding.

We knew that the aliens used alenium as a power source, but it was only after our study of their explosives that we realised that the power contained within alenium could be weaponised.
I'd now like to work on designing new alenium core grenades based on this information, which should result in grenades capable of inflicting incendiary damage as well as being more than twice as powerful as our traditional frag grenades.

Now that we have a good understanding of how to use alenium as a catalyst for our explosive devices, I think it's time we upgraded our standard c-4 explosives.
The resulting device will hopefully be as much as twice as powerful as our current loadout.

Now that we've completed our research on using plasma technology to create explosive devices it's time to put it into practice.
One of our initial plans is to create grenades using this theory.
When completed, it should be capable of causing more damage to its surroundings than it's alenium counterparts.

Replacing the alenium core of our explosives with one derived from plasma technology should lead to a substantial upgrade.
If all goes to plan, I'd expect to cause far greater destruction over a slightly increased area upon detonation.

Our newfound knowledge of fusion explosives has provided us with ideas for upgrading our existing explosive weaponry.
We've come up with a design which will incorporate our fusion technology into a grenade sized package. Once completed, it should provide for more damage upon detonation than previous grenades.

An attempt at integrating fusion technology with our existing heavy explosives has led us to an improved design for them.
It's still in the early testing stages, but results look promising, showing a greatly increased explosive yield over a marginally increased radius.

I'm sorry commander, but do your men really want to carry a miniaturised black hole around while in combat? That could be extremely dangerous if one went off by accident!
Well, if you insist. We can attempt to condense our work on singularity explosives down to something which will fit in a grenade, but this will take time to accomplish.
Yes, it will be extremely powerful, and no, i wont be testing it in here!

We've always considered black-holes or singularities to be dangerous, and nothing has changed to alter that now that we understand their principles.
We've already looked into using them with heavy explosives and they seem well suited for the task, however actually creating a portable black-hole is slightly more difficult.
We still need more time to perfect this application of the technology, but once complete it should be capable of destroying anything within its radius upon detonation.

I have an idea for a grenade filled with a caustic substance we believe will be effective against the aliens based on our chemical gas studies.
It should result in a weapon damaging to organics but harmless to buildings and terrain.
I still want no association with this line of technology commander, i'm just helping you to stay alive.

We've advanced our knowledge of how gases can be used to affect the alien invaders.
By replacing the original mixture with a new form of nerve gas designed specifically for this purpose our chemical grenades should become far more effective once a creature enters the cloud they generate.
We've also made improvements to the gases longevity under normal conditions, so expect the gas cloud to remain effective for longer periods of time.

Subsequent to our studies into heavy chemical gases we believe we can develop a grenade with improved capabilities against the aliens.
Once completed, it should be capable of more damage to any organisms exposed to it and the effect should remain in the area for longer before dissipating.

We've finished our research into extreme chemical gases and have come up with a plan for utilising it with our grenades.
Simply put, it should provide the best damage and least dissipation of all our chemical grenades once completed.

Further to our studies on the alien respiratory systems we've developed stun gasses capable of temporarily incapacitating them.
The next step is to weaponise it and I think modifying our existing smoke grenade design to hold this gas instead is a good place to start.

With our improved knowledge of the alien nervous system, we've developed a new gas to further incapacitate them.
We're currently working on integrating this formula into a stun grenade, and expect it prove far more effective than our previous design once completed.
Try to avoid this gas on the battlefield Commander as it has proven equally effective against humans.

With the development of our heavy stun gas, we should start upgrading our weapons to utilise it.
An upgraded grenade should be a simple enough task for a genius like myself. I expect it to have a greatly increased effect on organisms entering the cloud produced, rendering them unconscious more quickly.

We've now developed the perfect gas for neutralising the enemy. All that remains is to weaponise it.
I think we should start with a grenade, as its a relatively simple upgrade. Once complete, knocking out aliens from a distance should become much easier and the effects of the cloud should last longer.

We've applied our knowledge of plasma explosives to a less destructive item this time.
This upgrade should produce a grenade capable of creating a denser smoke over a slightly wider area once completed, thus providing enhanced concealment for your soldier.

Research into fusion explosives has given me an idea for upgrading our smoke grenades.
By changing the dispersion mechanism to one using fusion power, we should achieve a better spread effect from these grenades, thus increasing the lifespan of their cloud and making it more difficult to see through.

Singular explosives doesn't appear as if it would help us improve our smoke grenades. Entering a black hole tends to be fatal.
However, it has led to us conceiving of a method of condensing the amount of smoke contained within a grenade for even greater cover for your ground troops.
We still need to finalise it of course, but i expect it to work flawlessly once completed.

By applying the principles of plasma technology to flash bangs, we've come up with a new design for those type of grenades.
Once completed it should produce a far brighter flash along with accompanying noise resulting in a much higher chance of temporarily blinding or otherwise incapacitating any creatures close by upon detonation.

Now that we've completed our research of fusion explosives, we can apply it to our flashbang grenades.
In theory, a miniature fusion reaction should create quite a bright light along with a loud bang, both of which will be improved over the ones provided by our advanced flash grenades.
Of course we still need to test it and make sure it can be detonated safely, but i'm positive it will work out just fine.

Research into singularity explosives has led us to conclude that it is useless for flash grenades.
But, if we try to do the opposite and induce a miniature supernova, now that would be a huge improvement, and thanks to my genius, we are close to achieving this.
It will be better than our heavy flash grenades in every way once complete.

Now that we have developed a technology effective against alien electronics we need to weaponise it.
By integrating a device capable of generating an electromagnetic pulse into a grenade type housing, we hope to achieve a weapon capable of just that.
The initial pulse will be quite damaging to anything within its blast radius while the residue from its explosion will also effect anything entering it, but will dissipate quite quickly.

Our advanced knowledge of shock technology has allowed us to look at integrating it's principles into an explosive.
In theory this will generate a pulse with approximately triple the destructive power of our shock grenade, but is far bulkier and will need to be placed carefully.

Our original shock grenades wasted a lot of their EMP damage on a concussive explosion in their general area.
Now that we've completed research on electron technology, we can refine the blast to emit just concentrated EMP damage to any circuitry in the area.
This should result in almost double the effectiveness against robotic targets.

With our research into advanced electron technology complete, we can refine the blast emitted by our shock explosives.
Once complete the revised EMP should be twice as effective against robotic targets, and have a slightly increased area of effect.

With our increased knowledge of incendiaries I have an idea for a modified rocket capable of delivering a napalm-like payload.
This should result in severe fire damage to the immediate area around the point of impact.

Utilising our knowledge of alenium based explosives I believe we can upgrade our standard frag rocket to carry an alenium payload instead.
This should dramatically increase the damage caused to the target and its surroundings.

Our knowledge of plasma explosives has given me an idea for upgrading our rockets to utilize this destructive force.
If we replace the payload with a plasma generator, the explosion upon impact should be even more impressive than was achievable through the use of alenium.

Our research into fusion explosives seems almost tailor made for integrating into our rockets.
There are minor difficulties with keeping the payload inert until it makes impact with a target which we're still working on, but we should have it completed soon.
Preliminary testing has shown it to cause more damage over a wider area than plasma rockets.

Understanding Singularity Explosives has prepared the way to upgrading our current rockets to make use of this technology.
Once completed the rocket should create a small black-hole upon detonation, effectively destroying anything it comes into contact with.
I doubt we'll ever be able to create a more powerful rocket than this and initial testing has demonstrated a damage increase of 33%% over fusion rockets.

I've come with a design for a rocket which can house the stun gas we developed.
I'm sure your men will appreciate being able to stun aliens from a distance.

We have plans to upgrade our stun rockets to take advantage of the new gas we developed.
The gas itself has a higher chance of stunning any organic trapped in it, while the improved rocket design should increase it's initial dispersion upon impact.

Now that we've developed a more effective stun gas, it's time to weaponise it.
Replacing the gas in our existing stun rockets is a relatively simple process, but we've also redesigned the rocket casing itself to provide for greater dispersal and more immediate release of the gas upon impact.
We still have a few more tweaks to make to this design, but it should be perfected very soon.

We've finished research on an extremely effective stun gas and need to start adapting our current stun weapons to utilise it.
By redesigning our current stun rockets slightly and obviously replacing the gas with our latest mixture, I believe we can increase their effectiveness on the battlefield substantially.
Just tell your men to try to avoid the fumes Commander. It has proven equally effective against both humans and aliens in our lab tests.

We can utilise the same formula we derived from our chemical gas studies in a rocket.
We still need to make some tweaks to the rocket housing to ensure it can be safely fired by our rocket launchers and to shatter on impact, dispersing the caustic substance within.
I'll let you know when we're ready to begin field tests.

This new nerve gas we've developed is highly dangerous Commander, even more so than our original attempts.
In order to keep your men safe from it's effects we've come up with an improved rocket design so that it can be safely used on the aliens from a distance.
This new rocket should also improve the chemical damage caused upon impact.

Our research into heavy chemical gas is now complete and we need to devise a safe way to use it in the field.
Given that it's equally dangerous to our troops as it is to the aliens, i think a long-range delivery system would be best suited and so have started to work on designing a new rocket to carry our latest chemical gas.
Once completed, it should be capable of increased impact damage and improved dispersal of the gas itself.

We've designed the ultimate nerve agent Commander, be extremely careful around it as it will kill you just as quickly as an alien.
Given that you will want to keep your distance from its effects, we're working on an improved rocket design to enable you to safely deposit its contents amidst the aliens.
When finished it should provide almost perfect gas distribution over a wide area and the initial impact will also be more damaging.

We're currently attempting to apply what we've learned about Shock Technology to a rocket based delivery system.
If successful, it should generate quite an impressive electromagnetic pulse upon detonation, almost certainly destroying anything with electrical circuitry in its vicinity.

Using techniques gained from our research into Electron Technology, we've come up with a new rocket design.
The EMP is now completely refined and thus will inflict far greater damage on electrical circuitry with virtually no damage to any organism in it's area of effect.
It's ideal for dealing with Androns and alien mechs at a distance.

Based on data stolen from the sebillians and our own field test reports, I've designed an improved version of our alenium grenades.
The resulting weapon should have a slightly larger explosion radius, more force and also its construction should make the shrapnel that bit more penetrating against the aliens.

This new rocket model utilises enriched alenium derived from our studies on heavy explosives and successful field tests of our upgraded alenium grenades.
When completed it should be capable of delivering a payload almost double that of our existing alenium rockets and the shrapnel created upon detonation should be capable of increased armour penetration.

I've come up with a design for a new housing for our alenium explosives based on our recent research into heavy alenium explosives.
In theory this housing will focus the blast resulting in a tighter radius of substantially increased power which should make placement of them a little more forgiving on your troops.

Our recent hacking attempt on Sebillian computer files has managed to unlock some interesting reports on explosives. Combining this new information with field tests of our plasma grenades has led to the possibility of improving them.
If it works, our new grenades should deliver a more destructive blast over a wider area.

We've applied the principles used in our successful upgrade of plasma grenades to rockets.
This is a little trickier to implement as the casing required to contain the device in a stable condition as it travels at high velocities is considerably thicker.
If it works, the resulting blast will be far more powerful, but also contained to the area immediately around the point of impact.

Based on what we learned during development of our upgraded plasma rockets we've come up with a plan for upgrading our explosives as well.
This time the heavier casing is deliberate as it will allow us to channel the destructive force in a direction we specify causing far greater damage to its target while limiting the blast area.
Ideal for breaches where you wish to destroy the door, and not the soldier placing the charge.

By combining information we recently decrypted from sebillian data along with our recent fusion grenade design, I believe we can increase its overall damage.
If this theory is correct, it should produce a fusion grenade capable of damage and armour penetration over a wider area.
We're still working on making it a viable weapon, but testing should be completed shortly.

Now that we've successfully upgraded our fusion grenades, we can turn our minds to the task of applying the same principles to our fusion rockets.
Given that the procedure worked perfectly on the grenades, I have no doubt that we'll be able to achieve similar upgrades to the effectiveness of our fusion rockets.
The rocket will be designed to penetrate the target and have a delayed explosion, thus inflicting all of it's deadly force on the target itself, with little wasted energy directed to the surrounding area.

With both rockets and grenades already upgraded, we'll be applying the techniques used in both to upgrade our fusion explosives.
By shaping the blast through a combination of the physical casing construction and some ingenuity in the fusion reaction, we can theoretically concentrate the destructive force into a more powerful and more contained blast.
It should prove quite useful for blowing up specific targets, while leaving the area around it relatively intact.

We've now fully decrypted the sebillian files on explosives and have come up with a new singularity grenade design which should improve its performance.
As it's name implies, it will be a complete upgrade over our original singularity grenade and should be capable of delivering significantly greater damage over an increased area.
I'd advise your men to be even more careful while handling these grenades Commander, they'll be quite lethal once completed.

We're currently working on an upgrade to our singularity rockets after the successful implementation of our upgraded grenades.
This won't be an area affect rocket, rather it will be designed to penetrate the target, then activate a small singularity inside it.
The damage this causes should prove devastating to the target, but have little to no impact to anything close-by.

With our singularity grenades and rockets successfully upgraded, it's time to do the same with our explosive charges.
The packaging will be specially designed to feed the miniature black hole, thus increasing it's intensity but reducing its event horizon ... ok, in terms you can understand then ... it will cause more damage in a more compact area.
Lab tests so far have shown it be capable of causing over twice the damage of a conventional singularity explosive.

With our researches on electron technology completed, we've come up with a design for a new baton.
This new weapon should be capable of delivering an additional shock every time you strike something with it, thus increasing it's stun and EMP damage.
I'd advise caution on using it on electronics however, they tend to explode when their circuitry is overloaded which could be quite harmful to the person who just hit it.

With a live Xenomorph Drone to hand, I think we can manufacture a melee weapon capable of penetrating most alien armour by utilising the aliens chitin.
This process will obviously kill the xenomorph Commander, so if you want more of these weapons, you'll need to capture plenty of drones.

I have a plan to make our Combat knives more deadly Commander but there's a problem.
The amount of usable chitin we can extract from a Xenomorph is limited due to how their blood reacts upon death.
The outcome will be a much sharper blade, but at the cost of requiring more live xenos to create.

Our studies of a live Praetorian Xenomorph have led to some interesting theories for the creation of a new melee weapon.
Given it's larger size, we believe we can obtain longer pieces of useable chitin from its body which we can form into a sword-like weapon.
The praetorian's chitin is much stronger than that of a drone or warrior, so we also expect to be able to make the cutting edge if this weapon sharper, resulting in more damage and armour penetration than our knives while being swifter than our axes.

By further refining the blade produced from praetorian chitin, we can increase its armour penetration and the damage it will cause upon a successful strike.
WE're still testing our prototype in the lab, but expect to have it ready for field testing soon.
This process will naturally require more live praetorians to extract useful pieces of chitin from, so if you want more of these blades i suggest you capture more aliens for us to work with.

The armour or chitin of a xeno warrior is much more durable than that found on drones which has given us some ideas for a new type of melee weapon for your troops.
We believe we can extract enough chitin from a live warrior to create an axe, based on a medieval weapon design.
If successful, it should be capable of higher impact damage and armour penetration than our knife design.

By using smaller sections of alien chitin we believe we can refine our current axe design to achieve a sharper edge.
This should increase its impact damage along with its ability to cut through armour.
Obviously, this will require more live xenomorphs to extract the chitin from, but there's not much we can do about that.

We've come upon a further refinement for our axe design based on field reports.
By honing its edge we can achieve an increase in it's cutting power, but there's a downside to this.
Successful honing of chitin is hit and miss, as not all pieces retain their integrity during the process, so we'll need more live warriors to extract enough chitin to make one.

This is not so much an upgrade as it is a re-design.
We've discovered one section of chitin encasing a warrior which is perfect for our axe weapon. It's more durable and naturally sharp, so less honing will need to be done to it.
This should allow us to create an axe with a far better cutting edge.
The only problem is that each warrior only appears to have one of these sections of chitin, so it will require quite a few of them to create each weapon.

Following interrogation of a caesan physician, we believe we've come up with a way to increase the healing effectiveness of our first-aid packs.
We just need a little more research on the exact composition of the drugs involved to provide the optimum mixture.

Combining our knowledge of alien alloy hardening with what we've discovered about medium alien shields has led to a breakthrough with regards to our own shields.
While i won't bore you with the exact scientific principles involved in the creation of this new alloy, suffice it to say that it should be able to withstand up to 3 times as much damage as our traditional combat shield.

We've come up with an improved shield for you commander, well ... actually those idiots in engineering did, which they proudly presented to us.
I'll tell you the full story later, but with what they presented us with and what we know about alien shields we've developed a plan for a new shield utilising a combination of andron plating and alien alloys.
It should be considerably more resilient than our standard combat shields once finished.
I just wish those apes in engineering understood the difference between enhanced and enchanted ...

Now that we've upgraded our base facilities we can start to work on some designs which make full use of them.
To start with, we can upgrade our assault shield by applying what we've learned from alien alloy hardening to its construction.
We've also gained some useful data from large alien shields which i believe will help us to make this shield even better at stopping incoming fire.

We've come up with a new design for a shield based on what we learned from construction of our titan shield along with some new data gleaned from research into huge alien shields and andron intel.
I will need to check some of our specifications by subjecting that praetor you captured to another interrogation, but I believe we can have this new shield ready for production soon.

We will just have to distribute this shields to our men now.
Let me make some last changes ... .

We will just have to distribute this shields to our men now.
Let me make some last changes ... .

We will just have to distribute this shields to our men now.
Let me make some last changes ... .

We will just have to distribute this shields to our men now.
Let me make some last changes ... .

This is a curious device. It appears to protect whomever is holding it from a small amount of damage.
We'll need to study it further, but it might lead to some interesting innovations in our own shielding.

A slightly larger version of the alien shielding devices.
Perhaps with this we can improve our own shields.

This appears to be another example of their shielding devices and more powerful than its predecessors.
Study of this may well lead to improvements we can make use of in our own shields.
By studying this example of alien shielding technology we might be able to come up with ideas to improve our own shields.

The amount of energy this shield deflects is enormous, it's truly unfortunate that we can't replicate it and equip our own troops with it.
However, with some more study we may be able to emulate its effects thus enabling us to improve our own shields.

Given what we already know about alien alloys and electronics and using our newfound knowledge of how they keep their landing craft from crashing, obtained from the interrogation of a helpful caesan engineer, we've come up with a design for a new transport.
By utilising directional thruster arrays and alien electronics we believe this craft will be capable of speeds of up to 1500 mph, triple that of the chinook, while still being able to carry a full load. In fact we might even be able to squeeze a few more troops on board and still have enough space for a support vehicle.
I know your men are always eager for battle, so i'm sure they'll be delighted to hear that we can now get them there quicker!

We have a design for a new "dropship", only this time it really will be a drop ship.
It will be powered by a new type of engine based on alien fusion reactors giving it an increased max speed and constructed using hardened alien alloys but that isn't what makes it truly innovative. It doesn't need to land to deposit your troops to the battlefield!.
Utilising a new type of technology which we're creating using aspects of alien anti-gravity generators and information extracted from a caesan head engineer, your men will be safely "dropped" to the specified landing zone which will hopefully give the benefit of enhanced control over their initial deployment.
We still need to iron out some issues with the drop mechanism as dead soldiers tend not to perform very well in combat but i expect to have it ready for production soon.

Alien fighters are causing us serious problems in air battles and we need a counter-measure.
I've come up with a prototype interceptor which should perform better against craft constructed from alien alloys
The reduction in overall weight should allow for a faster aircraft with increased range and better manoeuvring in the air.
As its primary purpose will be dogfighting, we'll equip it with 2 hardpoints for mounting cannon type weaponry.

Alien craft have hulls made from alien alloys which our fighters are having a difficult time penetrating.
Because of this I've come up with a modification to the Mig-31 which will allow it to carry heavy torpedoes into the fray.
Due to the increased weight of the torpedoes, we'll probably have to remove the cannons to allow for stable flight, but that's a small sacrifice to make if we can shoot their scouts from the sky without needlessly exposing our aircraft to their return fire.

This downed fighter your men recovered after the airfight has given me an idea.
If we replace some of the internal systems with parts from other alien craft I think we can bring it back to a flyable state.
Our knowledge of alien alloys and electronics should allow us to repair its hull and internal systems, while an interrogation of an alien navigator has given us enough information to train a pilot to fly one.
Given their maneuverability they should prove to be an excellent replacement for our F-17's and appear to be capable of carrying a similar loadout as well.

I'm still amazed that you managed to bring down a terror carrier Commander. While going through the inventory of usable parts we recovered from it's wreckage, we came up with blueprints for a new type of interceptor based on using them.
If all goes to plan, it will be far superior to any of it's contemporaries capable of higher max speeds, range, turning speed etc.. We think it will also be capable of carrying both a cannon and 2 missile-type weapons into combat.
So why don't we go and start making them if they're so great, you ask? Well, there's a downside, first we need to finish our lab testing and second, we can only construct one by using the advanced alien systems available from a terror carrier, so the more you bring down, the more of these we can theoretically build.

We've analysed the structure of an alien medium scout and found it's armour to be thicker than the earlier version. Our conventional aircraft just don't pack enough punch to reliably bring one of these down, but i think we can do something about that by incorporating alien power sources into our designs.
Our current proposal which we've codenamed "Sonda" will be capable of carrying two missile type weapons into combat with its increased power and should prove to be faster and more agile in general over it's contemporaries.
We'll also be utilising alien alloys in it's plating so it should be more durable as well.

Following studies of a downed alien heavy fighter, we've come to the conclusion that our current fleet needs some improvement.
Utilising parts from downed alien ufo's we have designed a new interceptor based on our earlier asierus aircraft. This new aircraft currently titled "Corsair" should be faster and more agile than its predecessor and also more durable thanks to the use of alien alloys in its plating. As it will primarily be an interceptor we've designed it to carry two cannon weapons into battle.
We're only up to the prototype stage currently, but hope to have this project ready for action quite soon.

That light cruiser you recovered has caused us some concern. It's hull is far thicker than anything else we've come up against to date.
We've come up with blueprints for a superior long-range aerial bomber, capable of carrying our heaviest of air-to-air torpedoes into battle. It won't be much use in a dogfight Commander and will need to be protected, but should outperform the Lancer in every other way.
We hope to have it ready for initial testing in a matter of days.

Commander, I have some good news and some bad news for you.
The new fighters the aliens have accompanying their larger craft are far more dangerous than their predecessors, which we'll need to deal with.
The good news is that I believe we can sufficiently repair and retool one to use for our own purposes based on our research into alien power sources, electronics and alloy fabrication.
We're currently interrogating an alien pilot in order to obtain enough information to allow one of our own pilots to fly one.
As with the alien fighter, we'll have sufficient power to mount a cannon and missile type weapon on it, but it will be superior to the fighter model in every other aspect.

This is incredible Commander, you've managed to stop a terror battleship before it could devastate our cities.
To help celebrate this we sifted through the wreckage and have come up with a special aircraft design based on the parts we recovered codenamed "Lotus".
We believe that these parts will provide sufficient power to enable it to carry one missile-type and two heavy torpedoes into battle, which should make taking down the larger UFO's much easier.
Unfortunately, we can't fabricate these parts ourselves, so you'll need to supply us with more terror battleships to strip if you want more of these aircraft.

It appears that the aliens have stepped up their game with this new wave of UFO's they've been sending. After taking apart a wrecked alien hunter craft, we've come up with a design for a new fighter of our own.
By using our knowledge of alien reactors and alloy hardening we believe we can create a plane capable of matching the speeds of most alien craft, while also being more resistant to incoming fire.
Our current design will allow for enough power to carry a cannon and heavy torpedo into battle, so it will be capable of both dogfighting and taking down the bigger UFO's.

After dismantling a cruiser and examining all of its parts, we've come to the realisation that we need more powerful aircraft to help take them down effectively.
We have a new prototype airplane, nicknamed "drake"in development at present which might be the answer to this problem.
Using what we know about alien reactors, we can increase its power to mass ratio over earlier planes and hardened alloys should make it more durable as well.
We're currently trying to achieve enough power to allow it to equip both a missile and torpedo while still attaining higher flight speeds than earlier aircraft.

While i don't admire the aliens, on occasion they do have some good ideas. Our recent examination of an alien bomber carrier has given me an idea for upgrading our lancer heavy bomber.
Using what we know about alien reactors should provide the aircraft with enough power to equip two heavy torpedo weapons, while also increasing the crafts overall speed and acceleration.
It still won't be of much use in a dogfight, but we're increasing its damage threshold through the use of hardened alien alloys in its outer plating.

That hunter ufo you shot down appears to be similar enough to our own craft that a single pilot could fly one.
We're currently trying to patch one up with our existing knowledge of hardened alloys, alien reactors and electronics and are hopeful that it will be enough to restore one to flight capability.
I've also taken the liberty of questioning an alien Cruise Commander for information on how to actually pilot one of these craft which i will brief your pilots on once we successfully restore one.
As per the earlier alien fighters, it should be capable of equipping both a cannon and missile-type weapon, while being faster and more durable than before.

Congratulations on destroying an alien terror dreadnought Commander, that's one less city we need to worry about defending. Our examination of the dreadnought has revealed some interesting pieces of equipment which we haven't come across in any of their other craft and believe we can use to power a new aircraft of our own.
Based heavily on our research into alien fusion reactors our "Cyclone" aircraft should be capable of a higher top speed and acceleration than any of its contemporaries while also being able to carry a cannon, missile and torpedo weapon system into battle, making it extremely versatile and capable of almost any aerial combat role. This increased power has also allowed us to thicken it's hardened alloy plating, making it by far our most durable aircraft to date.
You already know what the downside is I'm sure. We can only create this aircraft by utilising the parts found in a terror dreadnought as our current technical capabilities are not up to recreating their hardware.

Now that we've had the opportunity to study an enemy interceptor, we've come up with some upgrades for our Marauder aircraft design.
Using our knowledge of fusion reactors and singularity cores i believe we can further increase its power to mass ratio resulting in greater acceleration and top speeds, while our advancements in alloy fabrication should also allow us to refine its armour plating to provide improved protection against enemy fire.
As with the marauder, this new aircraft, codenamed "contrail" will be capable of equipping a cannon and missile-type weapon.

While dismantling and alien battle cruiser, we noticed some improved technology in its design which we believe we can avail of ourselves to improve upon our drake aircraft design. The working title for this project is "nightowl".
We're upgrading it's engines using everything we've learned from research into alien fusion reactors and singularity cores and will use this increased power to allow us to increase it's armour plating with some help from our knowledge of alien alloy fabrication.
Once completed it should be capable of carrying a missile and torpedo weapon while still being faster than its predecessor.

Our study of an alien bomber battleship has shown us that the aliens have improved their capabilities and so we've been looking into doing the same. I believe that with some work we can upgrade our current bomber aircraft to be more effective against them.
This new design is heavily based on what we've learned of fusion reactors and singularity cores in order to allow it to attain a higher max speed along with carrying increased armour plating due to refinements made during the fabrication process of the alloys used.
Once complete it should be tougher and faster than our previous bombers, while still carrying a payload of two torpedo type weapons.

These alien interceptors are comparable in size to our own fighters and we believe that with a little work we can fix one up and use it for ourselves.
Interrogation of an alien fleet commander has provided us with enough information to brief a pilot on its controls, while our knowledge of alien alloy fabrication and electronics should allow us to repair the damage to its hull and internal systems. The propulsion system is a little trickier to fix, but i believe that utilising our knowledge of alien fusion reactors and singularity cores that we can manage it.
If this works, it should be capable of carrying a cannon and missile type weapon into battle.

Following questioning of both a caesan and sebillian fleet commander we now have enough information on their heavy interceptors to allow us to repair and pilot one.
The repairs will require every facet of knowledge we have on alien fusion reactors, singularity cores and electronics, while our research into alien alloy fabrication should allow us to restore its hull integrity.
Our examination of this alien aircraft allows us to believe that it will be capable of carrying one each of a cannon, missile and torpedo weapon, while still being considerably faster and more manoeuverable than any of our existing designs.

Utilising parts recovered from alien fighters, we've come up with a new aircraft weapon.
Sized to fit a standard cannon mounting this beam weapon will be about twice as powerful against alien hulls as our standard autocannon but with reduced ammo capacity

Based on our knowledge of alien hull construction, we're developing a rapid-fire high impact weapon
Due to design limitations, it will have a reduced range compared to our autocannon, but approximately 5 times the rpm and twice the damage and should be capable of being mounted on a cannon hardpoint

Following examination of the alien corvette's hull we think we need more powerful weaponry to penetrate it.
One of our ideas is for a "spear-gun". It will actually fire solid rods specially designed to punch through an alien craft hull.
The size and weight of these rods will limit it's ammo capacity and firing speed, but the damage caused in our tests was quite impressive.
Now we just need to figure out how to mount it on a cannon point.

We now know enough about lasers to start development of one capable of penetrating alien hulls.
We'll be using our autocannon as a base for the design so expect it to result in approximately the same overall damage, but with a faster rate of fire and hopefully increased range.
Put together, this should result in less time spent within range of alien return fire, thus increasing our odds of success.

Following examination of the wreckage from a strike corvette, we've come up with plans for an upgraded spear cannon.
Utilising alenium-tipped alien alloy coated "spears" with an improved firing mechanism, we can almost double the damage caused by our conventional spear cannon.
There will be a small drop in ammo capacity however due its the increased weight.

Now that we've completed our research on Plasma Technology we've come up with plans for an aircraft mounted plasma blaster.
Utilising alenium as a power source and constructed from alien alloys, we believe it'll be capable of achieving almost triple the damage of its laser counterpart per shot.
It won't be capable of firing as many rounds, due to power consumption issues, but should cause more damage overall.

Following study of alien heavy fighter weaponry, we've developed a plan for upgrading our existing fighter beam weapon.
It's should be capable of over twice as much damage due to increased energy throughput from an alenium power source, directed through an alien alloy fabricated barrel.
All things considered, i believe it will make our earlier adaptation of alien beam weaponry obsolete.

Following analysis of an alien lander UFO, we've developed plans for a new type of weapon. It's capable of emitting pulses of energy at a very high rate of fire, made possible by concentrating alenium energy through ... nevermind, Commander, I don't think you'll understand the concept.
It should be capable of relatively long ranges and a high rate of fire over a wide arc.

Following the study of the power-to-mass ratio evident in alien light shuttles, we've come up with a design for a cannon weapon with the power to rival a torpedo.
It will have some limitations however, firstly the amount of power consumed will severely limit the amount of shots it can fire, secondly, we're having difficulty maintaining the beam cohesion over long distances, so it will probably only be capable of short-range fire.
However, it should grant an option for equipping your interceptors with a weapon capable of penetrating the thickest of hulls once we've finished our tests.

With the recent development of MAG Technology, we've turned our sights to scaling it up to work with an aircraft and believe we've had some success.
While it's still in the prototype stage, this weapon appears to be capable of causing at least as much damage per minute as any of it's contemporaries while having a slightly increased range, which will hopefully make aerial engagements that little bit safer for the pilots involved.

Through a combination of gauss technology and alien alloy hardening, we've come up with a design for a new aircraft cannon.
This gauss cannon should be capable of longer range than the Mag Storm, while the reduction in projectile weight should enable you to carry more rounds as well.
It will also be capable of firing twice as fast but will see a reduction in damage caused per shot.

Following our study of an alien supply ship wreckage and the hardened alloys which comprise its hull, we're developing a weapon to hopefully negate its superior armour.
This weapon will fire a sonic wave at its target which will theoretically cause its particles to vibrate rapidly enough to cause its destruction.
It's still in the design phase at present, but should be capable of high damage at long ranges and be mountable on a standard cannon point.

We've analysed the beam weapon carried by alien hunter craft and believe we can adapt it for our own use through our knowledge of alien alloy hardening.
If correct, we should be able to produce a weapon capable of longer range along with double the fire-rate and ammo-capacity when compared to the heavy fighter beam.
There will be a slight drop in damage caused per round, but it should still be the superior of the two weapons.

Analysis of an alien cruiser has shown its weapons to be similar to our own spear cannons.
By modifying our design based on improvements evident in the alien version through the application of alloy hardening techniques to the spear itself, we can vastly improve the damage each shot will achieve.
The spears will weigh slightly more, so expect ammo capacity to be reduced accordingly.

Following our examination of a medium shuttle, we've come up with an upgraded design for our focuslense aircraft weapon.
This new version, the focusblast, will be capable of even higher damage, along with increased range, and still be capable of being mounted on a cannon point.
Ideal for turning a fighter into a heavy bomber.

Research into advanced pulse technology along with alien alloy hardening has allowed us to come up with a design for a aircraft mounted pulse weapon.
This should be capable of slightly increased range over the MAG Storm, but far greater damage at the cost of reduced ammo-capacity.
All in all, i think you'll find it to be the superior of the two weapons once completed.

We've come up with a design for a new aircraft cannon based on rail technology. It will be constructed from alien alloys and powered by a singularity core.
Initial tests have shown it to be significantly more powerful than our earlier Gauss Cannon, approximately 8 times more powerful at present.
However, the actual projectile is far heavier so your ammunition will be limited to ensure stable flight and it takes slightly longer to load a new projectile for firing. We're trying to improve on this, but only time will tell if we will succeed or not.

By integrating some principles from both rail and sonic technology into a single weapon, we've come up with a design for a particle pulse aircraft cannon.
As with all of our latest weaponry it will be crafted using alien alloys and powered through means acquired by the study of alien singularity cores.
It should be capable of an extremely high rate of fire along with high ammunition capacity, but each individual round wont be as powerful as some of our other cannons.
It will also have a very wide firing arc, ideal for strafing runs, but this versatility will result in reduced range when compared to most other cannon type weapons.

Following our examination of an alien heavy shuttle, we've come up with some improvements to our focus range of weaponry. We're calling this weapon the "short-circuit" due to the effect it has on anything it hits.
It will of course be constructed from alien alloys and powered through a means we've gained from examining alien singularity cores.
Testing to date has shown it to be capable of higher impact damage than most of our torpedoes making it extremely useful for taking down those larger UFO's while still being mountable on a cannon point.
As with our earlier models, this weapon will be restricted to short range fire and a limited amount of shots.
