Our study of the weapons aboard an alien interceptor has given us some ideas for upgrading our hunter beam weapon.
Based on alien singularity core technology, we can fabricate a new powered weapon utilising alien alloys which will be capable of approximately 50%% more damage than the earlier model. It might not be capable of charging quite as many shots, but the increase in damage will more than make up for that.

The weaponry we've discovered aboard the alien heavy interceptors is quite powerful for its size, but has given us an idea for upgrading our own beam weaponry.
By using some principles of alien singularity cores to power the a weapon constructed from alien alloys, we believe we can further improve the damage it can cause. Initial testing has shown it to be over five times as damaging to alien hulls.
This increased damage comes at a cost unfortunately, each shot will drain far more power than before, thus effectively limiting the amount of beams you can fire before having to land and recharge it.

The increased hull thickness found on alien battle cruisers has forced us to work on an improved spear cannon weapon for our aircraft. As usual, it will be powered using alien singularity technology and each spear will be formed from alien alloys making it capable of better hull penetration.
Once completed it should be far more damaging than earlier models and capable of long range fire, but ammunition will be limited as each spear will be quite heavy.

We've come up with a design for a revolutionary aircraft cannon, based on research into alien singularity cores, advanced dark technology and also ancient technology.
The new weapon will be formed using alien alloys and will be capable of a ridiculously high rate of fire. Approximately 12 times faster than any other weapon in our arsenal.
The ammunition itself will be quite small and lightweight, resulting in high ammunition capacity with low damage per hit. It should also be capable of hitting targets from quite a reasonable distance.

Alien fighters are agile enough to dodge our missiles mid-flight. Our planes can't match this agility so we've tried to come up with an alternative.
Based on point-defence technology we've come up with a design for a weapons-system capable of shooting alien missiles from the sky instead.
We're still trying to iron out some technical issues with this, and unfortunately, due to the bulk required to actually make it capable of tracking in an 180 degree arc it will need to be mounted in a missile or torpedo point.

We're now ready to implement our knowledge of alenium heavy explosives into weaponry for our aircraft.
Taking our sidewinder as a base, i believe we can replace it's payload with an alenium one for increased damage.
We haven't finalised the design yet, but it should be able to be fired from a normal missile point.

Following analysis of an alien medium scout, we've come with blueprints for a new type of missile weapon.
Its a short-range missile launcher, but capable of rapid-fire over a wide arc, which may come in useful against alien craft.

We've studied the wreckage of an alien light cruiser and designed a low-yield rapid-fire missile which you might find useful.
We're still working on the launching mechanism, but this missile will have similar range to a sidewinder.
It won't cause as much damage on impact, but their reduced profile means you can carry more of them and be capable of firing them up to 20 times faster.

Our research into alien alloy fabrication and plasma heavy explosives has led us to the point where we can upgrade our old alenium based missiles.
Utilising a plasma based payload contained in an alien alloy formed missile, this will be a complete upgrade of our alenium version.
To put it simply Commander, once this is finished alenium missiles will be obsolete.

Study of an alien heavy fighter along with alien alloy fabrication has given us some ideas for upgrading our anti-missile system.
We still haven't worked out all the details, but upon completion, it should be capable of a higher rate-of-fire, longer range and increased ammo capacity, all of which should make destroying incoming missiles that bit easier.

Research into heavy fusion explosives has given us all we need to upgrade our current aircraft missiles.
Once completed it should be capable of causing almost double the damage per warhead, with its only downside being a slight reduction in range due to the heavier hardened alien alloys used in its construction.

After taking apart a heavy alien scout, we've come with an idea for a new type of missile.
These mini-mines are capable of being fired over extremely long distances, while still packing a reasonable amount of damage per warhead.
Unfortunately, they are quite slow while mid-air, so i'd suggest not using them on ufo's with high evasion capabilities such as fighters.

Following analysis of an alien hunter wreckage, we've come up with a new design for a missile counter-measure.
We're calling it black titanium anti-missile due to the effect the alien alloy hardening process has on the colour of the projectiles.
Once finished, it will be capable of a higher rate of fire, longer intercept range and also larger ammo capacity, making it superior to the titanium version in every respect.

Based on the weapons systems present on an alien missile corvette, we've come up with an innovative missile design for our own aircraft.
It will be capable of being fired at a considerable range, far surpassing all earlier missiles, while also doing double the damage of our previous hyper missile design.
Honestly Commander, once this design is complete, it should render the hyper missile obsolete.

Alien singularity cores have lead us to quite a few new applications, from powering aircraft and weaponry to making things explode in new and interesting ways. We've decided to combine what we've learned from these strands of research to create a new missile for our aircraft.
When completed it should be more powerful than our fusion missiles, along with having slightly increased effective range and flight speed.
I really believe that we're now at the limit for how much damage we can hope to achieve from any single missile.

We've come up with an improved design for our anti-missile weapons systems following our examination of an alien interceptor along with research into alien singularity cores.
This new weapon will have the same range as earlier models, but with its increased rate of fire along with increased ammunition capacity it will be superior to all of them.
Once completed it should be installed on all aircraft you wish to have anti-missile capabilities.

We've been busy studying the weapons on an alien torpedo corvette and have come up with some modifications for our low sonic missile.
By utilising principles found in singularity core technology we believe we can double our previous rate of fire, and by using alien alloys to construct each missile we should be able to reduce their individual weight, resulting in more ammunition per missile bay, all while maintaining its damage output and range.
These factors combined should make this new missile superior to its previous models.

Research on an alien armoured scout has given us some ideas for upgrading our aircraft mini-mines.
By utilising aspects of alien singularity core technologies along with alien alloy fabrication, we believe we can increase the damage yield of each individual mine by approximately 33%% while suffering no discernible reductions to any of the weapons other specifications.
It's still in testing of course, but we hope to have it ready for production soon.

The weapons systems found on an alien armoured scout have led to some theories on upgrading our piranha missile system.
By replacing the power supply with that found in alien singularity cores and redesigning each missile to use alien alloys for the shell, we believe we can double its rate of fire and significantly increase the amount of missiles you can carry per bay with no downsides.
It will still be a short range missile, so bear that in mind when deciding where to use it.

Now that we have a better understanding of how alenium can be used in heavy explosives, I think it's time we considered upgrading our torpedoes.
We still have to work out the details, but if correct, this should be a direct replacement for our current avalanche torpedoes.

Research into heavy plasma explosives has given us some ideas for integrating it into our torpedo design
Substituting alenium with plasma technology as a power source should cause considerably higher damage, and our new torpedo design should have a slightly increased range.
We also have plans to greatly increase it's firing arc, which will come at a modest reduction in the rate of fire.

Alien Bombers are a menace, however, study of one has led to an interesting development.
We've come up with a new type of payload, based on anti-gravity generators. I won't bore you with the details as we haven't actually finished the design yet, but we have some projected outcomes based on testing so far.
It's relatively light weight means that you can carry more of them into battle and they can be launched from further away ... much further away.
The payload won't cause as much damage per individual torpedo but the increased amount of them you can carry should negate this.

Now that we've completed our research into the heavy explosives applications of fusion technology, we should be able to use it to upgrade our torpedoes.
There isn't really much to say about it commander, it will cause more damage, travel faster mid-air and will be capable of approximately the same firing range as its plasma predecessor, effectively rendering that model obsolete

Following an examination of the weapons systems aboard an alien bomber carrier, we've designed a new type of torpedo for our aircraft.
WE're calling it the neutrino torpedo and it will be a direct upgrade of our earlier gravity torpedo.
Once completed, it should be capable of higher damage, and its design will cause a reduction in the weight of each torpedo, thus allowing you to carry more of them into an engagement.

Research into heavy singularity explosives has given us some ideas for a new torpedo for our aircraft.
We'll be forming the torpedo itself using alien alloys and its propulsion system will be based on aspects of alien singularity core design. The new payload will be quite a bit larger than any of our previous torpedoes which should result in greatly increased damage, but the extra weight will result in being able to bring fewer torpedoes into an engagement.
Because of this i suggest you keep them for the larger and less maneuverable UFO's.

While examining the weapons systems of an alien bomber battleship we noticed some aspects of them which we might be able to introduce to our existing torpedo weaponry.
Using our neutrino torpedo as a base, we've come up with a design that will hopefully deal more damage, current estimates suggest a 25%% increase. The new torpedo will be slightly heavier but using technology gleaned from our research into alien singularity cores we should be able to maintain its range and flight speed.

Our troops need some armoured backup in the field but standard tanks are too heavy to transport by Chinook. We're going to look into modifying a Daimler Ferret to achieve this.
This should be capable of bringing heavy calibre machine guns into the battle and possibly rocket mountings in the future.
You can thank me later

Following extensive research in alien technologies such as electronics, power sources, alloy fabrication and information extracted from an alien engineer, we've come up with a blueprint for an upgraded Hunter Scout Car which we've codenamed "Seeker".
Using alien alloys for its plating should increase it's armour and an alenium power source will enable it to move faster, while its new integrated targeting system should increase its accuracy.
Feedback from your troops has indicated that they feel they carry enough light weapons into battle and that rocket support is what they need, so we're modifying it's mounting points to achieve this. We hope to have it ready to enter production very soon.

Given our studies on alien alloys and incendiaries we've come up with an idea for a more heavily armoured vehicle to accompany you on missions.
This new vehicle will theoretically be capable of carrying machine guns and also beam type weaponry.

The "Saviour" is an upgraded design of our existing defender light tank.
Research into alien reactors and electronics have given us the means to power this tank, while similar researches into andron servers and alloy fabrication have allowed us to upgrade its armour.
However, it was only through careful interrogation of both caesan and sebillian engineers along with data we stole from both race's computer archives that we've gotten it to the prototype stage.
Once complete it should be far more durable in the field along with being able to move slightly faster and be able to equip any weapon the defender could while its new targeting system should improve its accuracy.

During interrogation, alien engineers revealed some information to us concerning alloy fabrication which we believe we can use to create a light tank, codename "scimitar".
Utilising our knowledge of alien power sources, we've developed alenium power cells to propel it and adapted our knowledge of alien electronics to upgrade our targeting systems.
All of this combined should allow it to mount either high calibre machine guns or cannons, making for a versatile support tank.

Interrogation of an alien head engineer has provided us with information on the construction of their support vehicles which we believe we can use to improve our own.
This new project, codenamed "sabre" will be an upgrade on our existing scimitar tank design. Our knowledge of alien alloy hardening should allow us to vastly improve its armour and durability. We're also upgrading its internal systems with technology gained from our study of alien electronics. The engines will be a new design based on our study of alien fusion reactors and should allow it to move and turn more quickly.
Once completed it should be capable of firing any weapon that the scimitar could, but be far more efficient in combat.

Following interrogation of alien technicians along with information we've retrieved from hacking into their databanks, we've come up with a design for a heavily armoured siege tank light enough to be transported to the battlefield.
It's armour is a combination of alien alloys along with some improvements we've gained from studying andron servers, while its fuel cells and internal systems were inspired by alien power sources and electronics.
It's still under development, but once completed should be able to withstand most small arms fire and be capable of carrying heavy cannons to return the favour.

We've had a bit of luck Commander. Some of the information we retrieved from the alien computers has proven useful when combined with what we've learned through interrogating alien chief engineers and given us some ideas for upgrading our siege tank.
Using hardened alien alloys along with what we've learned from dismantling andron servers, we've massively improved both its armour and durability, while integrating alien electronics along with a new power source based on fusion reactors has allowed us to still keep it mobile and improved it's targeting systems.
As with the siege tank, we're going to make it capable of firing any cannon type of weapon.

We've come up with a design for a new type of weapons platform to support you in battle. We're calling it "hyperion" for now and i think you'll be impressed with it once its completed.
After an interrogation of a caesan chief engineer, I came upon the idea of integrating the concepts of singularity cores with directional thrusters to effectively create an anti-gravity field around an object. This new support vehicle will be the object in question and as such it will be capable of hovering over any terrain.
All in all, it should be quite effective in the field. For weaponry, it should be capable of equipping most of our weapon types, but it's not the most heavily armoured of our vehicles, so be careful when deploying it Commander.

We're in the process of designing a totally new type of support vehicle for the war effort, namely a piloted bipedal mech which we've codenamed "spiritwolf".
This design is heavily based on what we've learned from the study of various androns, particularly their heavy and terminal versions. The mech will be powered using technology gained through our research into fusion reactors, its targeting systems will utilise alien electronics and it's skin will be a combination of hardened alien alloys along with some modifications we've recently uncovered from interrogating a sebillian chief engineer.
We also need to design weapons specifically for this mech, as our current standard weaponry won't work with it's systems, but that hopefully won't take us very long.

We've come up with a design for a new mech following our interrogations of alien head engineers. Once completed it should prove vastly superior to our original spiritwolf mech.
By using hardened alien alloys for its armour plating along with some refinements gained from the study of andron intense models we can make it far more resistant to all incoming damage. We're also completely redesigning its targeting system with a new one incorporating our knowledge of alien electronics with those found in andron controllers. Finally, we're upgrading its motors with a refined version of an alien fusion reactor which should make it more mobile in the field.
All in all, this new timberwolf mech should completely outperform its predecessor in combat.

I have a blueprint for what i think will be the ultimate combat support vehicle in our fight against the aliens. While i could spend the next week going over every facet of research that was required to make this possible i don't believe that is a prudent use of our time, suffice to say it entailed a pooling of virtually everything we've learned from the aliens and also extensive hacking of their computers.
Once completed it should be vastly more robust than our earlier mechs while being capable of equipping more powerful weaponry, however the added weight of its plating will make it a little less mobile in the field. Not that it will make any difference of course, once it catches up to an alien, its improved firepower and armour should render the outcome inevitable.
The only real downside is that maintaining one of these mechs looks like it will be quite expensive due to all of the intricate systems which will need to be routinely optimised, but i feel the price will be worth it.

Now that we have a more complete understanding of incendiary weapons I believe we can create rockets for use with our Hunter Scout Car.
Just what you need for blowing up scenery or alien hull doors.

With our research into heavy alenium explosives now complete we can work on upgrading our existing mounted rockets for the Hunter Scout Car.
These should be an all-round upgrade to our original rockets

Plasma rockets are the future Commander, not alenium ones.
Following our research into plasma heavy explosives it's high time we upgraded our alenium rockets to utilise plasma technology instead.
Once completed I don't believe you'll ever want to go back to using alenium rockets.

With our research into theories on heavy fusion explosives completed we can work on upgrading our support vehicle rockets.
The increased payload of our fusion rockets will likely render previous versions obsolete as we believe we can maintain the same range and explosive radius as before while increasing their damage.

Singularities really lend themselves to the world of heavy explosives. By their very nature they achieve mass destruction over a wide area, which we intend to adapt into a new rocket design for our support vehicles.
Initial testing has shown them to be capable of a substantial increase in devastation over a slightly larger area than our previous fusion rockets.
We're in the process of designing anti-gravity field generators to help carry more of them into battle. While this will work while on the support vehicle, once fired, the mass contained within a singularity will exert its force, thus reducing their effective firing range, but it should still be sufficient for any ground encounters.

With our Division Technology based weaponry being such a huge success, we've decided to attempt to adapt it to higher calibre weaponry.
We have plans for a cannon which will have slightly increased range over MG mounts and much improved damage per shot along with some splash damage to the area around the point of impact.
The downside is that it will require a weighty vehicle to successfully fire it and not get blown backwards, but we're working on that.

Based on our increased knowledge of utilising alenium in heavy explosives, I believe we can upgrade our division cannon to achieve far higher damage upon impact.
The plan is to replace the standard core with weapons-grade alenium which should result in a larger and more powerful explosion, while also dealing incendiary damage to the surrounding area.
We still need to design a shell capable of this, but we should be finished soon. Any vehicle capable of mounting our kinetic cannon will be able to mount this instead.

By combining what we know of plasma technology and heavy plasma explosives, we have come up with a design for a new cannon.
If all goes to plan, this weapon will deliver a greater payload with increased force, resulting in more damage over a wider area than its predecessors.
We could also do with some new targets for testing Commander, our previous ones were all incinerated.

With our advancements in both gauss and pulse technology along with what we've come to understand about heavy fusion explosives, I believe we can start working on a new cannon type weapon for our tanks.
Our prototype has demonstrated increased range along with increased damage and armour penetration to the target, while affecting a slightly increased area than our plasma cannon.
The explosion itself wont generate as much lasting damage to the area, such as smoke or fire, so bear that in mind when using this weapon.

We're currently working on adapting the principles of heavy singularity explosives into a viable vehicle mounted weapon. Based on what we've learned from our research into advanced applications of rail and sonic technology, I believe we can achieve this.
If our theories are correct, this cannon will outstrip any of its predecessors in terms of range, impact damage, armour penetration and area of effect.
Unfortunately, the shells themselves are quite heavy due to the mass contained within a singularity, so you will likely be able to carry slightly fewer rounds into battle, but this is a minor consequence when considered against all of its benefits.
This weapon can and will cause extreme devastation to anything it hits, so be cautious when firing it.

Based on a Sebillian ballistics report we successfully decrypted, we believe we can upgrade our kinetic cannon.
This will involve replacing our conventional rounds with armour piercing ones which will deliver twice as much damage to the point of impact but cause very little damage to the surrounding area as well as having superior range.
More useful for taking out a high-priority target than for "glassing" the entire area.

We've come up with a new type of alenium cannon round following our recent hacking attempts on the aliens.
This new round should be capable of far better armour penetration and inflict almost double the damage of its normal counterpart and can be fired from a longer distance.
The only downside is that the majority of the explosive force will be concentrated on the point of impact.

This armour piercing development is brought to you courtesy of the aliens, won't they be happy to know how the information we stole from them is aiding our war effort!
In short, by making a few modifications to our Plasma Cannon, we can achieve better impact damage and armour penetration than before and also be able to fire the round from further away.
It won't deal as much damage to the surrounding area, but I believe that's a small price to pay considering its other improvements.

We've come up with a modified round for our fusion cannon based on information stolen from the aliens.
This new round will be capable of causing double the damage to its target over the normal fusion round, while also being far more able to penetrate the armour of anything it hits.
This increased armour penetration and damage is achieved by delaying the blast after initial impact which will result in the round being embedded in its target upon detonation.
The only downside is that the explosive force itself will likely be contained by the target's body or armour and not have much affect on its surroundings, but it's ideal for a pin-point kill when needed.

Sometimes our advancement in technology scare me commander, I'm not afraid to admit that. This is one of those times.
Our recent hacking attempts have turned up some valuable information about singularities which I've used to devise an upgrade to our singularity cannon.
This weapon can be fired from some pretty extreme distances and will likely penetrate and kill anything it hits. It won't do much damage to the surrounding area, but the damage it will do to whatever it is embedded in upon detonation will be quite lethal.
I suggest you be careful of where you aim it.

One of your soldiers suggested we look into upgrading our .30 calibre vehicle mounted machine guns based on our new X-Division technology.
After an initial look at the concept I believe we can achieve this although there are some issues with the scaling which we need to resolve first.
It will be a general upgrade to the existing machine gun and due to its modular design should be able to fit on any vehicle currently capable of equipping the .30 calibre version.

We've come up with a design for an energy based vehicle weapon based on our research into laser technology.
Scaling is an issue, but if successful we should be able to integrate it onto the Defender chassis.

Now that we've developed MAG technology we can take a look at implementing it on a larger scale, such as a vehicle mounted version.
Once its complete it should render our division mg obsolete with greater range, damage and armour penetration, and be mounted on any vehicle capable of mounting the division MG.

I've come up with a design for a new vehicle weapon based on our research into plasma technology.
It should be mountable on any machine-gun point, but will operate more like a cannon, dealing high-impact single shot damage to a wide area around the point of impact.

We're currently working on a new vehicle weapon which will utilise our research into gauss technology.
It should be equippable by any vehicle capable of carrying high-calibre machine guns, and each projectile will provide more damage and be better at penetrating armour than any of its predecessors.

Our research into pulse technology has given me an idea for a new vehicle weapon.
Our prototype has displayed far greater range than any of our previous machine-gun designs, while also being far more capable of penetrating armour.
Each beam might be slightly less damaging on impact, but with its increased rate of fire, I believe it will be a worthwhile upgrade.

By incorporating the principles of rail gun technology into a vehicle weapon, I believe we can create one better than our Gauss gun.
Initial testing has shown it to be capable of longer range along with modest increases in armour penetration and impact damage, making this the pinnacle of our kinetic vehicle weapon designs.

With our research into sonic technology completed, we've started looking at ways to implement it into our vehicle weaponry.
I've come up with a design for a cannon type weapon which will deal extreme amounts of energy damage to the target area, not to mention cut through most armours it meets.
Don't worry, it will be mountable on any machine-gun point, but we still need to figure out how to keep the energy discharge from knocking the vehicle backwards while firing.

We're currently working on adapting our vehicle MAG machine gun for use with our new mech.
It should be capable of similar range, but with greatly increased impact damage at the loss of some armour penetration.
However, the projectiles themselves will also be filled with a small amount of explosives so you should expect some additional damage to be caused to anything adjacent to the target.

With our developments in Gauss technology, we've come up with a new weapon for our mech.
It will has slightly increased range, damage and armour penetration over the MAG weapon, but each projectile is considerably heavier, so you won't be able to carry as much ammunition into battle.
Used wisely, it should be an improvement, just don't waste your shots.

Now that we can create effective rail-guns we've come up with a plan for one that can be mounted on our mech.
This was actually easier to design than weapons being carried by your troops as rail-technology lends itself to larger weapons. Once completed it should be superior to any of its kinetic damage predecessors in just about every way.

Recent advancements in Gauss technology have given us some ideas for upgrading our mech weaponry.
The increased power will allow us to pack each projectile with some heavy fusion explosives without reducing the velocity or range of the weapon.
This should lead to an increased area of effect for each round, along with increasing it's armour penetration due to a redesigned shell.

Our research into singularity heavy explosives has led to an innovation for our mech weaponry.
While it won't be actually firing singularities ... that many formed in close proximity might eventually grow enough to swallow the planet, it will be using some other improvements based on them.
Once complete, it should be capable of roughly double the armour penetration of the standard rail gun, while also affecting a wider area.

By combining certain advanced aspects of pulse technology with theories from heavy fusion explosives, we've come with a new weapon for our mechs.
It's an energy based weapon which will be capable of rapidly launching beams at a target while also dealing some damage to anything adjacent to it. It should also have a longer range than any of our kinetic mech weapons. Each individual shot will deal lower damage but with comparable armour penetration.

We've come up with a design for a new type of energy weapon for our mechs based on our current understanding of advanced sonic technology along with certain areas of using singularities as a heavy explosive.
While it's based on an entirely new branch of science, you can consider it an upgrade to our plasma cannon if that makes it easier for your men to understand, as it should be capable of outstripping it in almost every aspect, from damage per shot to the blast radius.
Its still undergoing testing at the moment but we hope to have it ready for production soon.

We've come up with some tweaks to our timberwolf railgun which should improve its overall performance.
The changes are small, but effective and mainly involve incorporating a new firing mechanism design based on information we stole from sebillian archives along with a new power supply based on alien singularity cores. These combined should result in approximately a 60%% increase in the weapons rate of fire, which will translate to a damage increase of the same magnitude should all rounds hit your target.

Our ion cannon is actually quite nearly at the cutting edge of our technology and making improvements to it is difficult.
Even replacing its power supply with a new one based on alien singularity cores won't achieve much by itself, however, we also had a little bit of luck with some files belonging to the caesans which we decrypted.
They're reports on energy manipulation, and while most of it is either already familiar to us, or un-usable by us, there were a few pieces of data which we'd like to try and implement in this weapon. If they're correct, expect it to have increased damage output over previous models.

Your men complain about feeling naked in the battlefield Commander, so I had an idea.
Unfortunately we can't yet use alien alloys themselves in our armours due to being unable to shape them but we might be able to achieve a similar effect by looking into using ceramic plates.
Perhaps in the future we'll be able to improve upon this once we learn how to mould alien alloys to fit our purposes.

Based on field tests and our new information on Alien Grenades, we've come up with an improved design for the Jackal armour
This should significantly increase the protection from explosive damage, but as a result reduce peripheral vision.

With the discovery of how to shape Alien Alloys, along with technical information extracted from our captives we can finally develop some new body armour for your troops.
Utilising andron corpses we have large enough plates of alloy which we can re-purpose into armour-plating.This will hopefully be a general upgrade in almost every aspect of the Jackal armour.
It should also help shield you from the effects of psionic attacks.
Your troops can thank me when it's done.

The discovery of aliens which can hover above the ground has forced us to look into flight ourselves.
Using our Wolf armour as a base, I believe we can create something that allows short bursts of flight.
The addition of jetpacks and fuel for them means we'll have to strip back the armour-plating a bit to keep its weight reasonable, but we'll endeavour to retain its psionic shielding.

With our knowledge of alien alloy fabrication and electronics along with what we've learned of andron server armour plating and their computers, we've come up with a revised design for our wolf armour, codenamed "direwolf".
Once finished it should provide superior protection against all types of damage along with a new HUD which should improve visual range under normal and night-time conditions. The new HUD will have a small impact on peripheral vision, but its benefits outweigh its costs.

Your troops are an ungrateful bunch Commander, I don't mind telling you. Were they happy with our Direwolf armour and how it helped protect them from enemy fire? No, instead they complained that it was too "girly looking".
Honestly Commander, i think they need to re-evaluate their priorities, but as it happens, we've come up with an upgraded version of the direwolf armour, project "alphawolf".
We'll be re-designing it using data we've learned from interrogating alien engineers and our study of heavy andron corpses.
... and it comes in blue!

We've come up with a more mobile design of our powered predator armour, codenamed "sentinel".
With what we've learned from interrogating a caesan chief engineer, along with advancements in alien alloy hardening and new plating methods discovered while studying andron warriors and terminals, we believe we can create an armour with good protection while still allowing a high degree of versatility.
We're also looking to incorporate information gained from our study of directional thrusters and anti-gravity generators to allow it to have limited flight capabilities. I'm sure your men will be impressed once it's completed.

We're currently working on tweaking our sentinel armour to make it more combat effective. While it's based mainly on the same technologies, such as anti-gravity generators and directional thrusters for flight and hardened alien alloys for some of it's plating there have been some new developments which we think will improve it.
Our research into andron controllers has given us an idea for a new HUD which should improve accuracy and increase your soldiers visual range both during the day and at night. We're also experimenting with replacing some of the plating with parts from intense androns.
Further to that, our interrogation of a caesan head engineer has led to an improved injection system for the chemical enhancements the suit can apply, which should further improve the reflexes and morale of the troop wearing it.

This is the blueprint for an upgrade to our warder armour. It involves mostly the same technologies, but with many little refinements to it to improve it immensely. It's flight capabilities will remain the same as they are still based on our understanding of anti-gravity generators and directional thrusters, but we're also incorporating them into the fabric of the suit as well to reduce its weight.
Our knowledge of alien alloy hardening combined with intense androns is now sufficient to enable us to completely rework and improve its armour plating. The HUD is still based on information learned from the study of andron controllers, but our recent questioning of a sebillian head engineer has given us some ideas for improving it. Finally we've further improved the chemical dispersal capabilities of the suit based on new information from a caesan head engineer which should improve the overall performance of any soldier wearing it.

Thanks to our research on heavy androns and their computers along with alien reactors, we're developing a new powered armour.
Utilising alien alloys to form the plating and alien electronics integrated into almost every part of the shell we've come up with what is almost a robot, it just requires a soldier to pilot it.
As it is powered, the pilot should find his or her strength greatly enhanced, which is just as well. One downside to this suit is that the sheer bulk of it renders the wielding or aiming of small arms virtually impossible.
Another problem is that in order to maximise protection, the visor area has been reduced which will have an impact on peripheral vision. But if you want your troops to return alive, we have no better option.

Now that we've finished interrogating both a caesan and sebillian chief engineer, we've come up with some upgrades for our predator armour.
Utilising plating techniques observed during examination of andron terminal and heavy models along with that found in medium drones, we can increase the protection provided by the original predator armour.
We've also come up with some more advanced targeting systems which should make aiming and firing of heavy weapons that bit easier, while also increasing the visual range of the soldier piloting it.

We've come up with a design for what we think is the ultimate personal armour. While it's closely related to our predator armour, almost every aspect of it has been improved upon.
Research into alloy hardening along with the armour found on intense androns has allowed us to greatly improve the armour plating of the suit. We've even improved its effectiveness against chemical weapons by studying the toxins used by a xenomorph empress.
It's HUD and targeting systems are largely based on those found in andron controllers but with some refinements made possible by our research into andron intel. We've also incorporated some of the information we gained from interrogation of alien head engineers into the design and believe it will essentially turn whoever wears it into a walking tank when completed.

You managed to capture a live alien!
Lets see what we can learn from it.

Now that we have a live guard we might hopefully be able to properly examine their armour.
Unfortunately, the dead bodies you returned to us were of limited use in this respect due to the amount of damage caused to them.
If I'm correct, this may allow us to design some new personal armours for your troops based on the aliens protective wear.

The armour of this soldier seems to be far more durable than what we encountered with their guards.
With a little luck we may be able to find a way to use this to upgrade our own armours.

The armour worn by the Caesans is both extremely durable and flexible.
We can't recreate the material they've used to create it, but we should be able to garner enough information from an examination to allow us to successfully extract decent quantities of the fibres from this warrior for our own use.

The armour protecting this Caesan is far bulkier than that of earlier versions.
With a little luck we should be able to extract quite sizeable quantities of their light fibres for our own use. However, care needs to be taken, previous experiments have shown that once damaged we have no way to reinstate its integrity.

The armour these terror soldiers wear appears to be of a different composition to that of the standard soldiers.
Our initial tests have shown that parts of it are composed of a denser, more resilient fibre. It may not be of much use for our personal armour as it would likely hinder mobility, but i think we can use it in some of our heavier armour designs, perhaps even using it to upgrade our support vehicles

The armour protecting this Caesan is far stronger than anything we've encountered their race wearing to date.
With some careful procedures, I believe we can obtain reasonable amounts of useful material from it which we can use to upgrade our own armours.

Considering the density of the fibres used in the armour protecting this caesan, I'm actually surprised that he could move at all during a battle.
We need a little more time to study this but hope to be able to gain substantial quantities of the fibres their armours are composed of from subsequent captives.

The quality of the armour worn by this chieftain appears to be far superior to that worn by their soldiers.
We need some time to study this and ascertain exactly how they've achieved this improvement.

This armour is quite impressive. Lightweight, durable and also exhibiting a high tensile strength.
With some further study we should be able to extract as much usable fibres as possible from each subsequent captive.

Just like humans, their leaders have better armour than the grunts.
Sorry Commander, that wasn't directed at you.
.... Anyway, we hope to be able to obtain large amounts of useful material from its armour, once we manage to cut it away from him.

It can teleport over short distances you say? Are you sure your men weren't hallucinating ... or intoxicated?
I guess we better start the interrogation before it teleports out of here!

The armour encasing these Wraiths appears to be far denser than that found on sebillian or caesans.
We need to study this if we ever wish to beat them.

I'm still nonplussed by how these aliens are capable of teleporting while wearing body armour such as this subject is.
Further study will hopefully allow us to determine how they've managed to achieve so much mobility.

The fact that they can teleport is frightening enough, but they also have extremely durable armour as well.
With some more comprehensive examination of them we may be able to utilise those principles in our own armour.

The aliens appear to equip their terror operatives better than their ordinary minions. The armour encasing this wraith is far better than that seen on its contemporaries.
With a little further study we should be able to discern how this armour was made.

I'm actually amazed you managed to capture this alien alive commander. His armour is quite impressive.
We need to study it more in depth, but i believe we can make use of the technology involved in its construction.

The armour this wraith wears far surpasses anything we've seen previously on them. I still can't believe that they're capable of teleporting around a battlefield while wearing it.
We'll take it apart piece by piece in order to ascertain exactly how they can still be so mobile while so heavily protected.
They appear to be the snipers of their reality, maybe we can learn something from interrogating one.

While their armour appears to be a solid plate, initial examinations have shown it to be composed of fibres of varying strength.
Further analysis may enable us to use this to our advantage.

Even though their "plates" are composed of fibres, they're still far stronger than anything we can manufacture at present.
We need to study this further to be able to extract as much useful material as possible from every captive you bring us.

The sheer stopping power of the armour this alien is encased in is quite impressive.
Now, if you wouldn't mind stepping back a little, we need to cut him open to fully examine it .... the results will be worth it commander.

This harridan was really kitted out for battle. It's armour is amazing.
We need to research it further, but it appears to be composed of equal parts of light and dense fibres.

The fact that harridans can fly in this armour is quite astounding. While it is composed of light fibres for the intersections, the main plating is mainly composed from their dense fibres.
The weight alone should negate flight, but perhaps with some more study we can understand how they've managed this.

The armour this alien is encased in is truly impressive commander. Not only is it lightweight enough to allow flight, but it's also durable enough to stop most conventional rounds.
We really need to study this phenomenon more deeply.

This creature you've brought us looks extremely deadly, and the reports from the field say that they're capable of some sort of biological attack now, transforming its victim into a cocoon of sorts.
are you really sure you want to try examining it while it's still alive? One mistake could unleash it on everyone here.

We've been thinking about how reapers are actually able to turn normal people into zombies, not to be confused with how any distraction at all can turn our engineers into zombies.
We believe its a venom of sorts contained in their claws, but will require further research to verify this and make use of it.

The toxin contained in a reapers claw is really quite potent. With some further study I believe we can extract that toxin and turn it to our own uses.
By "our", i mean "your". I want nothing on my record where chemical weaponry is even remotely suggested.

This might not be the toughest of reapers, but it is by far the scariest for the population. It's toxin is capable of taking out anyone it hits in a single stroke.
We might be able to weaponise that with a little more study.

You managed to capture a live alien!
Lets see what we can learn from it.

Sebillians are tough, especially considering their natural regenerative abilities, and the armour this guard is wearing makes them that little bit harder to defeat.
We already have some idea of how their skin protects them so it'll be interesting to see how this armour is constructed. Hopefully we'll be able to make use of some of its concepts in our own designs.

The armour worn by these soldiers is actually remarkably similar to that found on the other species even though it looks completely different.
We need to study it further to fully understand how its constructed.

As we've seen earlier, this armour is actually constructed from fibres and not plates. Unfortunately we have no way to actually create these fibres however some further study should provide us with the means to successfully extract as much as possible from every sebillian you bring us.

The amount of armour this sebillian is wearing is amazing. While it looks quite bulky and heavy,in actual fact its extremely lightweight.
If we can study this further we may be able to extract enough from it to use in our own armours.

The armour worn by sebillian terrorists is actually far harder than that worn by their ordinary troops.
We believe that this is made possible by the introduction of a new fibre or possibly an alloy of some sort and will need further study to determine the truth.

Our initial examination of sebillian terrorists has shown us that their armour is far more durable, not to mention that they appear to have been genetically engineered for this role, being larger and stronger than all other sebillians encountered to date.
We need to study them further if we wish to make use of this information, particularly where their armour is concerned as it appears to be custom made for them and may provide us with some insights we can use in our own designs.

This creature is actually quite terrifying once you realise that its sole purpose in life is to cause harm to others.
Even it's protective armour is specifically designed to provide it with the maximum flexibility while still providing astounding amounts of resistance to most types of damage.
We need to study this further in order to make use of the concepts evident in its design.

The sebillian chieftains wear a more "complete" set of armour when compared to their soldiers.
The armour itself appears to be of the same grade or quality, but because there's more of it to work with, we hope to be able to extract more usable resources from this subject.

Ahh, one of their officers at last.
His armour appears to almost completely protect his body leaving only the hands and parts of the face uncovered. Even with this amount of protection, it appears from your reports that he was still highly mobile in battle so I'd like to take some time to study this.
I believe that we'll be able to extract some substantial quantities of lightweight fibres from that armour he's wearing which we can use for our own projects.

It looks like they do actually care about those of higher ranks among the sebillians.
The armour protecting this leader is quite comprehensive and it actually surprises me that you managed to take one alive with it all intact. We need to study it further but i'm certain we'll gain lots of useful material ... from both it and the armour.

This robot is fascinating commander! Study of it's construction could help further our collective knowledge immensely.
Even if we can't fully understand it's electronics, it's carapace alone could help lead to innovations in our body armour designs.
Shall we get started?

Initial examination of andron plating has shown that its not actually a metallic plate at all. Instead it appears to be composed of dense fibres woven in a way we don't yet fully understand.
We'll rectify that as soon as we start to work on this andron.

We need to further our study of how aliens are able to weave these fibres into such dense plating.
Once completed we should be able to use it to upgrade the armour of our existing support vehicles and possibly even some heavy personal armour as well.

This appears to be the warrior caste among the androns just going by the extent of heavy armour plating he's encased in.
Further research should prove me correct, and will likely provide us with ideas for upgrading our own body armours.

This andron is encased in even denser armour than the warrior version.
Study of this new armour will almost certainly help us with the development of our own powered armours and vehicles.

The armour on this andron is quite impressive.
I believe that we can successfully extract substantial amounts of usable fibres from it once we've finished our studies on its composition.

I think the aliens are adapting to our firearms Commander, the armour encasing this andron is almost twice as durable as that evident previously.
With some further study we may be able to emulate them, or at the least use some of their technology against them.

This is a very important find Commander!
Study of this unit's circuitry should help us to better understand alien electronics and communications.

We need to take this alien construct apart to determine how exactly it differs from previous models.
However, just from initial inspections, it appears to have an upgraded outer plating which may provide us with ideas for improving our own armour plating for vehicles and body armour.

This unit has even more intricate circuitry than the server model.
Study of this may enable us to enhance our existing vehicles and personnel armour and perhaps even lead to developing better ways to destroy androns in combat.

This appears to be the highest level or grade of andron. It's really difficult to apply ranks to an automaton but its circuitry is certainly more intricate than that found in all previous models.
This might be the breakthrough we need for creating better armours or vehicles to support you in battle.

This appears to be the warrior caste among the androns just going by the extent of heavy armour plating he's encased in.
Further research should prove me correct, and will likely provide us with ideas for upgrading our own body armours.

This andron is encased in even denser armour than the heavy version.
Study of this new armour will almost certainly help us with the development of our own powered armours and vehicles.

Now that we've analysed the circuitry in andron units I think we can start to make some progress on understanding how their computer systems work.
This may even help us to upgrade our own lab equipment if we can successfully integrate them with our own infrastructure.
Or perhaps create powered robots or suits of our own, who knows what may be possible.

You captured one Commander, I'm impressed. Perhaps now we can find out something useful about them.
Their corpses were informative, but unfortunately dissolved before we could do much, however, with a live one I think we can start to develop some improved melee weapons based on their chitin.

This drone appears to be slightly more resilient to our weapons, which is bad, but perhaps we can turn it to a good use by making use of its natural armour for our own purposes.
Don't look at me like that commander, they are the enemy afterall!

While this xeno is even stronger than its predecessors, unfortunately, its death tends to corrode almost all usable pieces of chitin before we can take it away from them.
We're still refining the process, not to mention still trying to dodge their tails during their death throes.

This appears to be far stronger than the drone type of xenomorph, although thankfully its also slower.
Research of its blood may enable us to map out the aliens dna which we could then use to develop weaponry to exploit any weaknesses found.
Failing that, we can also look into its armour plating and see if we can find something useful from it.

Unsurprisingly given the size disparity, we believe that we can gain far more usable chitin from a warrior than from a drone.
There is a downside though, warriors really, really don't like being stripped of their skin, which i can empathise with.

This warrior is far superior to the red versions we encountered earlier, quicker, deadlier and more vicious.
Unfortunately, it's just as capable of exploding into a ball of acid which really doesn't help our scientific efforts to understand them ... or use their armour.

This is an extremely intimidating creature Commander.
reports from the field suggest its capable of withstanding far more damage than its smaller cousins. Further research of it should enable us to determine if that is due to its armoured carapace or something biologically different about it.

Commander, I have something to say to your troops! While i agree that putting a shotgun blast through the face of any attacking alien is good practice, it's also bad for our scientific progress.
Take this alien you recently captured for example. While its chitin is exactly the same as any previously caught, its teeth or fangs are notably sharper.
We might be able to use them in future melee weapon experiments.

This xeno is far more dangerous than its red compatriot, however we're encountering difficulties with it.
Its blood also appears to be more vitriolic which makes obtaining useful parts from it difficult.
Perhaps some further research might remedy this.

I'm amazed that your men were able to capture this creature Commander.
Study of it will hopefully increase our knowledge of these xenomorphs.
At the very least, we should be able to find more effective ways of killing them.

You captured the red queen? The tsarina herself? ... Ok, enough joking, i am actually impressed Commander.
We're not sure yet exactly what we can get from her, but her fangs and armour look to be in good shape so I'm sure we can come up with something.
Who knows, maybe we can even make a new type of sword from them.

OK, i take back everything i ever said about your troopers. If they managed to capture this thing alive, then i'm seriously underpowered.
Joking aside, i think we can make some use of this creature, particularly its fangs which may be useful for our new melee weapons range

This appears to be a more advanced xeno than the drone, be wary while facing one.
Study of it may enable us to expand our knowledge of xeno dna.

A very dangerous xemomorph Commander, I'm surprised you managed to catch one alive.
We may be able to enhance our knowledge of xeno dna through examining it.

This is a very impressive xenomorph specimen you've captured for us Commander.
I'm sure that study of its biological systems will increase our understanding of how these aliens operate and hopefully lead to better ways of combating them.

This appears to be the ultimate authority among the xenomorphs Commander. Study of this magnificent creature should allow us to finally fully understand them.
XXDescriptionXX

This short stocky creature which we've nicknamed a "bull" is a new type of weapon being unleashed by the aliens.
Further analysis will be required to determine its purpose on the field.

A slightly smaller version of the reaper alpha, however it seems to be far more damage resistant.
We'll need to study it more closely to determine any other special characteristics it may possess.

We've now completed research on the drone, warrior and praetorian class of these creatures.
We think this has provided us with enough data on them to be able to reconstruct an accurate model of their dna which will hopefully allow us to combat them more effectively.

With our studies into some of the more advanced xenomorph classes completed we can now start to map out its dna chain more completely.
Hopefully this will give us some new insights into ways to combat them.

Now that we've captured both a reaper and its smaller cousin, the reaper bull, we can map out a model of their dna chain.
Analysis of this will hopefully suggest ways to deal with them more effectively in combat.

With both a rhino and alpha of the reapers captured, we can update our current understanding of their dna.
This might prove useful in developing more effective ways of combating them.
We're being attacked Commander! We're currently going over initial reports on what has occurred and should have a better picture of the situation for you shortly.

A new element and you say that the aliens power things with it? Interesting...
Well, I'm sure that if I apply my genius level intellect to uncovering it's secrets we'll be able to make use of it ourselves.
Why are you still here Commander, don't you have more Alenium to bring me?

Our initial attempts to shape alien alloys met with failure, as I'm sure you're aware commander.
But with our recent studies of alenium and information gained from some captive alien technicians, I think we can succeed this time.
It will take some time to set up the project and be a little expensive, but i think the costs are worth it.
We really need to be able to shape alien alloys if we wish to use them for our own equipment in the future.

While we have had success in the shaping of alien alloys, the process by which we melt them also weakens them.
With the recent capture of an alien engineer, I believe we can ask them specific questions about how they shape their alloys in order to enable us to return them to their full strength.
If we can achieve this it should enable us to create far better armour plating for our aircraft, vehicles and personnel.

I've read your reports from the battlefield about Alien Hull and Weapon durability and have finally had a chance to examine the materials used in their construction.
It's absolutely vital that we understand this material if we ever intend to beat the ET's
Just think Commander, we could construct our own weapons, armour and planes from this, not to mention the Nobel Prize I'll obtain for this endeavour.

With what we've learned from examining alien computers and andron hubs we're now very close to understanding alien electronics.
This may prove vital in the future so I'd like to talk to that technician you captured to confirm a few theories.

Subsequent to autopsies carried out on the creatures which accompany the ET's and discovering potential weaknesses they exhibit, I believe it's essential that we look into developing incendiary weaponry.
Fight fire with fire Commander, or in this case, fight beasts with fire!

I have a theory based on what we've already learned from our studies on alenium and alien grenades.
If correct, we should be able to produce a more powerful replacement for our standard c-4 explosive.

Our new alenium explosives are powerful and pack quite a punch, but i have an idea for improving upon this design.
If we're successful the enriched alenium should enable us to create more powerful versions of our existing explosives.

We've now studied the workings of alien reactors, advanced grenades and alenium explosives.
I believe this is enough to work with to enable us to adapt our plasma Technology into generating an explosive force.
If successful we should be able to make upgrades to all our existing alenium grade explosives.

By expanding upon what we've managed to achieve with the development of Plasma Explosive Technology we think we can increase its yield.
This could prove very useful for improving our larger weaponry such as those mounted on vehicles or aircraft.

Our study into alien reactors has revealed that they use a form of fusion to generate massive amounts of power from relatively small amounts of alenium.
By combining this with what we know about their heavy grenades we may be able to develop a new explosives technology for our own uses.
Now that we've established working theories on using fusion reactions for explosive devices, we think we can refine it a little more through some further research to increase the explosive yield.

We've come up with a theory which may result in a new type of explosive we can use for our weaponry. Its based on our research into alien singularity cores combined with what we've learned from studying their extreme grenades.
If the theory proves to be correct, it should revolutionise human explosive theories in general, and also have the far more practical effect of allowing us to implement it into our existing arsenal.

With our initial studies of singular explosives we've gained the potential to create minor explosive munitions based on the technology. Our research should now focus on scaling the designs up so that we can hopefully use it on our larger weapons such as aircraft missiles or vehicle weapons.
With just a little more time and effort, I believe we can achieve this feat.

You've returned a lot of different alien corpses to us commander, which has enabled us to form a rough idea of how their various cells operate.
With some study on the common characteristics displayed among them, I believe we can further our knowledge of how they function and perhaps find a means to incapacitate them.

Following our studies of alien biology and finding out what makes them tick as it were, I believe we now have enough information to create effective stun weapons.
We really need some live captives Commander if we ever wish to understand and beat them.

I believe we have now captured enough specimens of the aliens various races, including a doctor, to allow us to really explore their genetic coding and find out what makes them tick.
Who knows what this may lead to in the future ...
XXDescriptionXX

Now that we've studied live specimens of both the Reaper and it's larger cousin the Reaper Alpha we've come up with some theories on how they "reproduce".
We still have some questions which we'll need to get answers to from their medical experts, but if we're correct it should enable us to battle all organic aliens more effectively.

Congratulations on managing to subdue that alien base commander.
I think with some study of it we can determine which parts of it would be of benefit to our own technologies and perhaps even inspire us on ways to improve our own base facilities.
Thankfully, we already have an alien engineer in captivity which should help identifying what's useful far easier.

This communications device you secured for us is really quite important commander.
With what we've already learned of alien base and andron construction we might finally be able to figure out how the aliens send transmissions to each other.
This discovery might even eventually lead to us being able to decode inter-ship messages while UFO's are in flight!

Now that we understand how an alien communications array works, we're working on developing a listening device which will enable us to intercept communications between attacking UFO's.
It's based heavily on our understanding of electron technology and will take some more time to get an operational prototype ready for testing, but if correct, we should be able to determine the precise loadout and intention of any invading craft once it's complete.

With our research into alien bases, andron computers and electron technology all but completed, we've come up with some designs which we can apply to our own base facilities.
If successful, these should increase our research and manufacturing efficiency, while also enabling us to look into some of the more advanced technology researches which we just don't have the equipment for at present.

We've extracted enough information from alien captives to begin to understand how alien power sources work. With a little more time I believe we can unlock their secrets and start to make use of them in our own designs.
If we ever want to be able to create better vehicles or aircraft it's vital that we complete our studies on these.

Given what we know about alien power sources and what we've recently learned from an alien engineer we believe that with a little further study we can learn how to deconstruct them.
This will likely provide us with some additional alenium ... and clear our storehouse of power sources we no longer require.

This appears to be a scaled up version of an alien power source.
With some study and a little help from a captive engineer, we might be able to implement these into our own designs.
This could potentially enable us to create more advanced aircraft, vehicles and possibly even powered armour.

Not all of our designs require the amount of power provided by an alien reactor.
Following interrogation of an alien chief, we believe it may be possible to strip down a reactor to its basic components
This will be a complicated process and needs some lab testing to be carried out but will hopefully provide us with some additional alenium and alloys.

This is even more powerful than the standard alien reactors, the increase being gained through some form of fusion.
If we can emulate this we should be able to use its increased power to upgrade our support vehicles and airplanes.
I need to return to interrogation and get some more information out of that chief engineer you captured, but it shouldn't take much longer.

Following our recent interrogation of an alien head engineer, I think I've come up with a way to strip one of their fusion reactors down.
If this proves to be successful we should be able to disassemble any unwanted reactors and retrieve some of the alloys and alenium used in making them for you to use elsewhere.

I've just learned from an alien chief engineer that one of the pieces of equipment recovered from a recently downed UFO is in fact what enables their ship to traverse outer space. We're going to call it a hyperdrive for now.
Further research of this "engine" is essential if we ever wish to be able to take the fight to the aliens and end this war.

An interrogation of one of the engineers you captured has helped us to identify the purpose of one of the items you recovered from a recent ground mission.
Apparently they use it to create an anti-gravity field which allows whatever it's connected to to hover above the ground, from their drones even up to the scale of some UFO's
We don't understand how it actually generates this field yet, but are working on it right now.
This might enable us to create armour capable of short periods of flight and possibly even be used for upgrading our dropship design.

This appears to be some sort of power source, not only for the craft it was found in, but also for it's weapons systems.
I think by pooling the information we extracted from an alien chief engineer along with what we've discovered of this device so far, we should be able to come up with a theory on how it works and possibly make use of them ourselves in the future.
If we succeed it should help us with development of any new powered items such as vehicles, aircraft and their weapons, and it has some intriguing characteristics that also may be useful in explosives technologies.

This curious device was quite a mystery to us up until quite recently. Under questioning, an alien technician informed us that it's used to make small directional or vector adjustments to their ships while in flight.
This would be of very obvious benefit to us in the design of improved aircraft and hover vehicles and potentially powered armour capable of flight as well.
But all that is in the future, first we have to figure out how it works, but have no doubt, with my intellect on the case we shall succeed.

Given what we already know about stun weapons and with our new knowledge of alien stun grenades, I think it's high time we developed our own weaponised stun gas.
Wouldn't your men appreciate being able to stun aliens from a distance rather than whacking them over the head with a baton?

Study of these new grenades you've recovered from crash sites should enhance our knowledge of stun gas.
When completed, I'm sure we'll be able to improve upon our existing weaponry.

Now that we've completed our study on alien heavy stun grenades we can start working on a new stun gas formula of our own which will hopefully be more effective against the aliens and pave the way to upgrading our existing weapons which make use of stun gas.

I think that by studying this extreme alien gas grenade we might be able to upgrade our own stun gas technologies such as grenades and rockets.
We just need to understand the composition of this gas first, and see if we can incorporate it into our own stun gases.

Study of xeno corpses and a live reaper have given me some ideas on a new gas which could be used against them.
If it works commander then i expect you to be happy and to keep quiet about its development.
chemical warfare is a taboo subject among the nobel prize committee.

Through the study of alien toxin technology and the dna of reapers we've arrived at a better understanding of how their nervous system is put together.
With this information in mind, we've started working on designing a new chemical agent which we believe will be more effective against them.
Obviously, once completed, we can upgrade our existing chemical weaponry with the new gas.

We've learned some fascinating information regarding how alien organisms operate through our study of xeno dna, alien blood technology and also the horrific zombification abilities of the reapers.
By combining all of this, i believe we can work on developing a gas which will be far more effective at attacking their nervous systems thus making it easier to kill them.

With our knowledge of alien hybrid technology combined with everything we've learned about xenomorph and reaper dna i believe we can start working on creating the ultimate chemical gas to use against the invaders.
If successful it should make taking down any of the organic aliens much easier although we'll still have to develop working delivery methods to use it safely.

Study of this grenade may enable us to further our understanding of alien biology, specifically how to stun them.
I need to talk to that Caesan medic you captured commander, he should have the information i require.

We've carried out some tests on one of the advanced alien stun grenades.
Actually we used it on a Caesan physician and after he woke up, we threatened to repeat the process unless he explained the nature of the gas to us.
Yes Commander, it was cruel, but I'm sure it was less so than what happens to any humans they capture.
With a little more study of the information he's provided us with we should be able to improve our understanding of alien stun gasses and perhaps improve our own stun technologies.

Further to our interrogation of a caesan doctor along with the study their heavy stun grenades we're now close to understanding how the gas works.
Further study will hopefully allow us to develop our own improved stun gas for use against them.

I have some more questions for that Caesan professor you captured Commander.
If i can get enough answers we may be able to safely examine the gas present in their extreme stun grenades without unduly exposing any of my techs to un-necessary risks of inhalation. It should be needless to say, but understanding the chemical composition of the gas may enable us to improve our own stun gases.

These alien blood grenades are quite dangerous to all organic life they're used against. We're currently questioning a captive sebillian medic about their origins and may have some leads soon.
If we can understand how they work, then maybe we can start work on developing new chemical agents which can be used to fight the aliens.

Between what I've learned from that Weapon Sergeant you captured and this grenade you recovered from the battlefield, I think we can increase our understanding of how alien explosives work.
This should lead to being able to mass produce our own versions of this weapon.

We've questioned that weapon officer you captured on the properties of their advanced grenades and found out some useful information.
With a little more study and experimentation I believe we can use this knowledge to enhance our understanding of explosive principles in general.

Interrogation of an alien weapons commander has given us some insight into how their heavy grenades function.
Further research will hopefully allow us to adapt these principles into our own explosives technologies.

Following an interrogation of an alien tactical commander, I think we now know enough about their extreme grenades to take one apart.
We were hesitant to do so before as getting it wrong would have resulted in some pretty severe damage to our lab equipment along with the likely death of any tech close by.
If we can successfully study it, we may discover some new theories on explosives which we could use for our own such weapons.

This grenade seems to be used primarily by wraiths and a recent interrogation of an alien weapon commander has given us enough details to begin safely dismantling and studying it.
