We need to question this alien carefully Commander.
As one of the leaders of the invasion, he's sure to have some information regarding their overall plans.

Commander, a silent alarm has been activated at the secret base entrance, and i can see an alien walking towards it with his hands raised on our security monitors.
If possible try to bring him to me alive and we'll see what we can get from him.

Commander, I'd like to have a word with you! I'm sure by now you've realised that we need live alien captives to interrogate if we ever wish to understand why they're really here.
This presents us with 2 problems, the first is figuring out a way to communicate with them, which I will deal with myself.
The far more vexing problem is that we'll need containment units constructed IN HERE by those cretins from the workshop.
I'm not happy about letting those glorified grease-monkeys anywhere near my lab equipment Commander, not happy at all!

This Alien was a squad leader of sorts among their races. An officer if you will.
We'll need to question him carefully and try to extract as much information as possible.
We really need to know the true intentions of these invaders so that we can counter them effectively.

This appears to be a low-level leader of some sort among the Caesans.
Interrogation of him might lead to some useful information.

Interrogation of this alien will hopefully provide us with details of their intentions.
With a little luck, he might even know something about accessing their computer file.

This is one of the leaders of the invasion, well done Commander.
Hopefully an interrogation of him will lead to more information regarding the overall purpose behind these attacks.

This was the Caesan running the operation? Very well, we'll question him carefully.
If we're lucky he might know enough to enable us to infiltrate their systems.
It's possible that a close interrogation of this Caesan will help us gain access to their computer systems.
He might know something about their overall plan Commander. I think we should interrogate him as soon as possible.

This was the mastermind behind the recent attack on our cities?
While I'd like to kill him right now, he may prove to have valuable information for us.

He thought he could storm in here and kill us all. Thankfully, we're not as defenceless as we seem.
Our techs are already coming up with ways to thank him for his visit and who knows, maybe he'll know enough to save himself.
So this is the alien responsible for the recent bombings. While i'm sure you'ld like to torture him, it possible that careful questioning may pull some interesting information from him.

The alien computer systems are impossible to hack Commander, I'm sure you know that.
But as chance would have it we've stumbled upon a certain phrase used by recent captives.
Perhaps it will grant us access to some of the data concerning energy weaponry contained in their databanks.

We've had a stroke of good luck Commander. One of my techs was walking by when your Caesan captive started spouting what initially seemed like gibberish.
He had the good sense to write it down however, and using this we think we can access a small portion of their energy weapon files.

Welcome Commander. Following on from yesterdays interrogation of that Caesan one of my techs attempted to hack into a captured computer.
The man is either an idiot or a genius, I haven't decided yet, but he guessed at a 123 password from something the alien said.
in all the known universe no-one is stupid enough to use 123 as a password, but it appears to have granted us limited access to their files on energy weaponry.

Fortune has favoured us Commander! That Caesan you captured yesterday actually knew some of the passwords required to access some of their data on energy manipulation.
With a little study this might enable us to enhance our own knowledge in this field.

We'd like to try running a decryption algorithm on some of those files we managed to retrieve from the Caesan computers.
We'll be basing this algorithm on certain key phrases we've noticed your various Caesan captives using during interrogation.
Perhaps we'll get lucky on some of them.

One of your caesan captives said something which reminded me of a cryptology lecture i attended a few years back.
I've tried accessing one of their files using a few techniques i recall from then and actually managed to gain limited access to one.
While incomplete, it appears to contain scientific data on experiments involving something called caelium which might prove useful to us in the future, but a lot more study is required before we can be sure what the specifications in this file mean.

We've had a bit of luck translating some of the files stored on an alien computer.
One of those caesan captives we interrogated actually new part of their encoding algorithms, which should allow us access to some of the data contained within.
Initial indications are that its contains statistical data on energy weapons which we may be able to use to enhance our own energy based designs.

Following extensive interrogations of the many caesans you've captured, we've almost cracked one of the files stored on their computers.
It appears to be a report on energy manipulation which may be of some use for our own energy based technologies.

A recent caesan captive provided us with part of a pass-phrase which we've linked with what we extracted from an earlier captive.
Our initial attempts at using it have given us some access to data on energy based applications.
Further study is required to fully translate these files, but may prove useful for our own energy technologies.

Those files we discovered on an alien computer have had us stumped for months.
But thanks to a little fortune, not to mention our tireless efforts in questioning caesan operators, we've finally managed to crack one of them.
We still need to fully decode and translate it, but it appears to be a report on high-end energy generation which we may be able to make use of in our own energy based technologies.

One of the caesan operators you recently captured actually knew the entire pass-phrase to access one of the databanks of their computers.
We're currently going through its contents to see if there's anything useful there we can make use of among all their astral navigational data.
It will take some time to complete the scan, but we have already found one file on energy beams which may be of some use.

We came across a few phrases used mainly by caesan operators while going over transcripts of their many interrogations.
We're trying to use them to gain access to the files on their computers and have some limited success so far. One of the files we've uncovered had some data on their energy weaponry which may come in useful in the future.
We're still trying to unlock the rest of the files on the system which will take some time to complete, but hopefully we'll gain access to more of their data.

This operator appears to be in charge of missions which require a landing craft, such as supply runs.
Perhaps with further questioning we can gain some useful information on the computer systems found on those craft.
Cruisers are powerful craft and dangerous to face. Perhaps the operator you captured will know enough to help us to combat them?

This Caesan was in charge of operations for the entire base you captured him in.
I'm fairly certain interrogation of him will reveal detailed logistical information we can potentially make use of.

We've captured the mastermind behind their recent terror attack.
By applying a little judicious pressure, I'm sure we can convince him to tell us everything he knows.

So they thought they could break in here and kill us in our sleep? Well, they were wrong.
I'm sure the leader of the attack has some valuable information we can use, all that remains is to extract it from him.
This is going to be fun ... just not for him!

This caesan must have access to their computers in order to co-ordinate air strikes.
If we're lucky we might be able to extract this from him.

This ceasan was the one in charge of the mission you apprehended him on.
Interrogation of him may lead to some information we can use or perhaps even grant us access to their computer files.

Capturing this caesan was a good idea commander.
Our initial talks with him revealed that he was in charge of data encryption for their entire base.
Hopefully we can extract enough form him to allow us access to the files stored on their computers.

This was the caesan in charge of the recent terror attack.
Close questioning of him might provide us with some information we can use against them.

We captured this caesan while he was trying to access our computer systems.
Perhaps interrogation of him will allow us to return the favour.

If he was able to co-ordinate bombing attacks among their fleet then he must have access to their computer systems.
Interrogation of him might force him to reveal some of their secrets.

He appears to have been in charge of communications on board the battleship.
Interrogation of him may yield some information we can use.
This was the operator aboard that dreadnought you attacked. Interrogation of him may grant us access to their computers.

Ahh, the alien in charge of all communications going through that alien fortress you attacked.
With him in our custody perhaps we'll finally be able to access their computer systems and look through their files.

I really despise the aliens behind those terror attacks that plague our cities.
I'm sure that we can persuade him to tell us everything he knows.

I'm very glad that you captured this caesan, Commander. It turns out that he was the one in charge of the recent assault on our base.
We have some special treatment in store for him to show him our thanks. I'm sure that we'll know everything he has ever learned by the time we're through.

This caesan was in charge of operations aboard one of their bombers.
Interrogating him may reveal enough information to grant us access to some of their computers.
Interrogation of this captive should help us in understanding how their energy weapons function.

Caesans seem to understand a lot about energy manipulation.
I'm positive that with careful questioning of this weapons officer we can improve our understanding of these theories.

He appears to have a wealth of knowledge on the weapons which caesans use in battle.
With some careful questioning we should be able to extract this information from him and try to adapt it to our own ends.

This caesan might know about their high-end energy weapons that they've recently started using in battle.
Only time will tell, but hopefully he'll know enough to allow us to start some real research into their properties.

This is the alien that piloted the UFO you captured him from.
I'm not sure if he'll know much that's of use to us, but perhaps we could learn how to operate their craft. I doubt we could ever operate one of their larger UFO's but perhaps we'll discover enough to enable us to do something with their smaller fighter craft.

This pilot appears to have detailed knowledge of how their heavy fighters operate.
With enough questioning we might gain enough information to turn any captured heavy fighters to our own purposes.

He says that he was only a pilot and that we'll gain nothing from him. I tend to disagree.
With some further interrogation i think we might learn enough to operate one of their hunter craft.

Capturing this alien might prove to be very fortuitous.
Our initial questioning has revealed that he knows quite a bit about operating their interceptor craft. With some further pressure, I believe we can make him tell us all he knows about them.

We need to be careful while interrogating this subject.
He appears to know a lot about how they use their alloys in manufacturing their weapons and crafts.
Gaining this information is invaluable to us and could lead to countless improvements on our existing arsenal.

The technician class of Caesan appear to have a detailed knowledge of almost every aspect of alien technology implementation.
With this in mind, careful interrogation of this engineer could potentially provide us with almost limitless useful information we can use in our own designs.
Just make sure he stays alive until I say I'm finished with him.

This was a chief engineer among the caesans.
Going by earlier interrogations, we believe we can learn a lot of useful information from him relating to nearly all aspects of their technologies.

He appears to be a very high ranking engineer among their race.
Going from past experience, their engineers tend to have information we can implement in our aircraft, vehicles and armours. Hopefully this one will be the same.
This alien was a medic among his race. With careful questioning he might provide us enough information on their biology to enable us to combat them more effectively.
Interrogation of this Caesan should lead to improvements in our understanding of alien physiology and perhaps our own medical capabilities

This caesan might have some interesting information we can use on their chemical and stun technologies.
If so, then we will hopefully be able to use it to enhance our own weapons based on those technologies
Interrogation of this caesan might provide us with information we can use to further our medical or chemical sciences, only time will tell.
There's a chance that this soldier knows enough about their weapons to enable us to start understanding how they work.

These terror warriors seem to use a different class of weapon in battle.
With close questioning, we might be able to determine how some of them function.

This is the most dangerous Caesan i've ever encountered. I suggest you be wary of them on the battlefield.
Perhaps with a little questioning he'll reveal soem information on the equipment he was carrying before being captured.
This sebillian may have some knowledge of how their computer systems work. Careful questioning will be required.

This sebillian was in charge of more than just the operation during which he was captured.
Careful questioning may reveal more of their overall plans for us and perhaps gain us access to his crafts computer system.

This sebillian was a leader of sorts among his race.
Interrogation may reveal some of their overall strategy to us.

While he may have been in charge of the operation he's still just a step above a grunt.
But all sebillians seem to have a keen understanding of ballistic weaponry, so he might know something of use.

It's possible that this sebillian might be able to help us gain access to their computer systems.
Provided he's stupid enough to help us of course.

He's a low ranking overseer of some sort, but perhaps he'll know something about how their systems work.
I'll let you know if we find out anything useful.

This despicable creature was in charge of that recent terror attack. We'll find out what he knows.
Considering what we have planned for him, he'll definitely talk.

This alien appears to have been in charge of the attack on our base Commander.
While we have some wonderful plans for it, let's see what it knows first.
If he was in charge of the recent bombing runs, then perhaps he knows a thing or two about their weapons technology.

While going back over notes from your recent interrogations, I chanced upon a phrase they used which struck me as odd.
It appears to be a keyword of some sort which I'd like to try out on their weapon systems.
If i'm correct, we may gain some valuable data on UFO weapon systems which we can make use of.

The encryption on the Sebillian Weapons systems is frustratingly hard to break. Hell, it might not even be encrypted at all, its just in a language we don't yet understand.
However its not all bad news, one of my techs tried entering a phrase used by your latest sebillian captive into the computer and seems to have access to some data on ballistics.
this data is still encrypted, but with some study i think we can decipher some of it.

We just got very lucky Commander, and i hate relying on luck.
After our interrogation of that Sebillian specialist I played back the recording while standing near one of their weapons systems computers.
Something he said woke it up and displayed a file on what appears to be ballistics reports.
Further study of this file is required, but i believe it may lead to us being able to improve our own ballistic weaponry.

Like some people around here, Sebillians aren't exactly noted for their intelligence, Commander.
However cracking open their files is proving incredibly difficult and time-consuming!
Yesterday we forced a sebillian captive in front of one of their computers and ordered him to access it. He just looked at us blankly.
This morning we tried it with a different captive and he understood enough to access one file on the system. It's almost a lottery deciding who knows what.
We're still deciphering the information in the file, but it looks like being a ballistics report of some sort.

I'd suggest you be careful which sebillians you terminate during a mission.
Given their lack of innate intelligence it would appear that the alien in charge of the UFO's computer system is chosen purely at random and so gaining access to this data boils down to chance.
As luck would have it, the sebillian you captured yesterday was such a one and we're working on the files he accessed for us as we speak.

We've managed to gain access to a portion of a sebillian computers storage device.
It appears to contain statistical data on different ballistic weapons which might prove useful to us once fully translated.
You really don't want to know how we gained access to this ... the odds of it happening again are astronomical.

Two of our recent sebillian captives happened to know parts of a pass-phrase between them.
Using this we've gained some access to a file containing ballistics reports.
Further translation is needed, but it may prove useful for upgrading our own ballistic weaponry.

Thanks to a little luck we've gained access to part of a sebillian computer data-bank through interrogation of various of their operatives.
The file is still encrypted, but we're working on that now. Initial translations seem to indicate that it contains data on alien ballistics which might prove useful in our own designs.

Following the interrogation of numerous sebillian captives, we've finally managed to crack one of their databases.
So far the information appears to be related to ballistic technology, but we'll know more once it has all been compiled.

Some of the sebillian operators we captured recently had enough information to allow us to start guessing at possible pass-phrases used to encrypt their computer files.
We're using this process now, but it will obviously take some time to complete the task on all of their data. One of the files we've managed to unlock so far appears to be about their kinetic weaponry which might be of some use to us in the future.

We got lucky during a recent hacking attempt of the aliens computer systems. One of the sebillians you captured knew part of the access code, and a lab tech guessed the remainder of it.
Unfortunately, it only unlocked a small folder which appears to contain data on ballistic and kinetic weapon theories. I'm sure this will come in useful once we decipher it entirely, but i really wanted to gain access to all of their files.

We had a bit of luck in cracking open one of the alien files based on information gained from interrogating various sebillian operators.
It appears to contain data on experiments the aliens have been carrying out on their kinetic weapons. I can't be certain if it will be of any use to us yet, but even knowing where they met with failure might provide us with some insights of our own.
Interrogation of this sebillian may provide us with some clues to scanning alien computers. Seeing as he was in charge of operational logistics, he'd almost have to have access to them.
Being a relatively senior rank among his crew I'm hoping that we'll be able to gain useful technical information from questioning him.

Interrogation of this sebillian might lead to data we can use on their computer systems.
Or he might be as unknowing of details as half the captives you bring here are.

This sebillian was in charge of the recent terror attack you apprehended him at.
Such an attack requires a lot of co-ordination, so hopefully he has knowledge of how to access their computer systems which undoubtedly contain this information.

They thought attacking us was a good idea.
Well, we captured the leader of that attack and are going to convince him otherwise.
After we see if he has any useful information for us that is.
Questioning of this sebillian may provide us with access to the targeting computers of the UFO he was in charge of. Only time will tell.

This operator may have some useful information on how their computer systems work.
We'll begin questioning of him immediately.

Apparently this sebillian was in charge of all logistical operations pertaining to running their base.
Questioning of him may reveal some data we can use pertaining to this.

The creature behind the recent terror attacks.
I'm sure that if we ask him "nicely", he'll become very helpful.
He might even know how to access some of their computer files.

We caught this sebillian trying to hack into one of our turret targeting systems to turn it on ourselves.
If he has that much knowledge of our computer systems, then perhaps we can extract information from him regarding their own ones.

Co-ordinating aerial bombing runs on our cities takes quite a bit of background work.
I believe that interrogation of this sebillian might gain us some useful data on how they achieve this.

The advanced computer systems found in carriers need a more detailed knowledge of them to operate.
With that in mind, i believe this sebillian may be able to provide is with information we can use to access them ourselves.

I really don't rate the individual intelligence of any sebillian very highly Commander.
However, seeing as this one was in charge of communications aboard that dreadnought, perhaps he does actually know something useful. I'll question him and find out.

This sebillian almost has to be smarter than most. Managing the logistical requirements for an alien fortress would of necessity demand it.
With some careful questioning we might be able to gain information we can make use of from him.

I see you managed to capture the ringleader of that recent terror attack.
We have quite a few things to say to him. I don't think he'll enjoy most of them, but it should persuade him that its in his best interest to tell us everything he knows.

So this was the leader of that recent base assault. We have some fun things planned for him, although i doubt he's going to enjoy them much.
If nothing else, he should become very talkative before we're finished with him. I wonder if sebillians can sing?

This was the crypto "expert" aboard one of their bombers.
I still don't think highly of the cognitive abilities of any sebillian, but perhaps we'll be able to extract something useful from him during questioning.
This sebillian appears to be familiar with their weapons technology. Interrogation might reveal some insights on how they function and allow us to further our own knowledge on small arms.

All sebillians seem to have an innate aptitude for ballistic weaponry.
It's possible that interrogating this weapons officer will lead us to new developments for our own ballistic technologies.

This sebillian seems to have been a quarter master or weapons commander of some sort.
He appears to have detailed knowledge on the workings of their ballistic weaponry and we should try to extract as much of that as possible from him.

This sebillian actually has some in-depth knowledge on some of their current weaponry.
We need to question him further, but i believe we'll learn enough from him to allow us to advance our studies of their kinetic weaponry and start to generate ideas for improvements of our own.
He appears to have been a pilot of one of their smaller craft. With a little luck we should be able to extract enough information from him to learn how they operate.

Apparently this sebillian is quite familiar with the controls of an alien heavy fighter.
Interrogation of him might lead to us being able to adapt those craft to our own ends.

During initial questioning, he revealed that he was the pilot of the UFO you captured him on.
I doubt we can safely operate their larger UFO's, but perhaps we can learn enough from him to operate one of their smaller craft, such as their Hunter.

He has some fairly extensive knowledge on all of the operational parameters of their various UFO's.
With further questioning, I believe we can extract some useful information from him and perhaps learn enough to operate their interceptors.

He appears to be quite knowledgeable for a sebillian. I think that with careful questioning we can gain a lot of useful information from him regarding their weapon systems and perhaps even their craft

This sebillian is a member of the engineering caste of their race.
We've found in the past that this caste is the most knowledgeable about the workings of all facets of their technology ... unlike our human engineering caste who prefer to tune cars with greasy spanners.

He appears to have a higher standing among their class than the technicians or engineers.
I think he might know more about their technical capabilities than what we've gained from previous interrogations.

This sebillian has quite a lot of detailed information on their mechanical units.
Further questioning will be required, but I'm hopeful that the information we gather from him will lead to innovations in our own vehicle and powered armour designs.
He appears to have detailed knowledge of alien biology. If we can extract it from him who knows what it may lead to in the future.
Interrogation of this sebillian might provide us with information on the physical capabilities of the various creatures who accompany the aliens.

As a doctor of his race, He might have some in-depth knowledge of sebillian chemical technologies.
We need to question him on this if we wish to be able to counter the weapons they've been using on us.

This appears to be a soldier class sebillian who's been trained for special operations.
Interrogation of him might provide us with some insight into the purpose of the weapons they employ on terror attacks.

He appears to be more heavily armed than the terror soldiers we encountered previously.
Interrogating him might reveal how some of the new weapons they've started using on the battlefield function.

The armour and weaponry found on this alien seem to be quite a bit more advanced than earlier soldiers we've encountered.
I'll see if he has any knowledge on either of them under questioning.

A spec ops version of the harridans. These creatures are deadly at long range.
Interrogation of him may yield some information on the weapons they use.

These harridans appear to carry more advanced weaponry into battle.
Questioning of it may help us to understand how these weapons operate.

The weapons this harridan carries into battle appear to be quite deadly.
We hope to be able to force some information on them from him during our interrogation.

This wraith has been specially trained for terror attacks.
Interrogation of him might provide us with some insight into the weaponry the use during such attacks.

A deadly foe on the field with its teleport ability coupled with new weaponry.
We might be able to learn something of these weapons through interrogating it.

This is the most advanced form of this species we have encountered in the field to date. His weaponry and armour are quite impressive when compared to earlier encounters.
We hope to ascertain how they've been upgraded during questioning to see if there are any principles involved which we can make use of ourselves.
